title: pork chops and kraut bake
directions: Brown chops in drippings in large frying pan. Salt and pepper. Combine kraut, apples, onions, brown sugar and caraway seeds. Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Place chops on sauerkraut mixture. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and continue baking 15 minutes or until chops are done. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except for one package of dried beef.
Form into ball and roll in leftover beef.

title: mother's macaroni or potato salad
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients well. Then add carrots, pepper and peas.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chocolate caramel drops
directions: Microwave caramels and whipping cream in a large bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir until caramels are completely melted. Be very careful you don't burn them. Cool. Place pecan halves on lightly greased cookie sheets in clutters of three. Spoon caramel mixture over nuts leaving ends showing.
Spread melted chocolate over caramel mixture. Let stand until chocolate is set.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on top of stove until thick. Pour in ovenproof bowl.
Top with meringue and brown.
This is a good way to use up old bread.

title: orange cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream together lemon and orange rinds, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add to flour mixture. Add lemon juice and milk.
Beat well.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chili-beef rolls
directions: Saute ground meat and onions until meat is brown and onions are cooked.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, brown sugar, tomato sauce, chili powder, brown sugar, dry mustard, lemon juice and celery.
Simmer, stirring frequently, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
If necessary, add cornstarch and water to thicken.
Serve on grilled or toasted frankfurters rolls or hamburger buns.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
With a sharp knife, remove stems from mushrooms.
Combine crab meat, parsley and onion.
Stir dry mustard into mayo; toss with crab mixture.
Fill each mushroom crown with a tablespoon of crab mixture.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix water, oleo and cocoa in pan. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add flour, sugar, salt, soda, eggs and sour cream. Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lisa's pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan put a layer of crackers.
Mix Cool Whip with pudding. Put half of mixture on crackers.
Put another layer of crackers. Repeat pudding layer and another layer of crackers.
Finish with chocolate icing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hungarian frosting
directions: Cook milk or juice and flour until thick (like paste).
Add sugar and Crisco, then flavoring.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix ingredients together and put into a 9 X 13-inch greased pan.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Bake at 200° 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes until finished.

title: emma boque's sugar cookies
directions: Roll and cut into shapes and bake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir together. Refrigerate for four hours before serving with crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute the onion in a small amount of olive oil.
Cook the potatoes in 1 1/2 c. of water.
Add the onions to the potatoes (and water), and cook until potatoes are tender but not falling apart.
Lower the heat and add sour cream and chicken soup. Gradually add the milk, salt and pepper while stirring constantly. Heat the mixture but do not boil.

title: orange almond salad
directions: * Stir-fry almonds in sugar in a skillet.
Stir constantly over low heat until coated, glazed and browned.
Put on wax paper, cool and break apart.
Store covered.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Layer lasagna noodles, meat mixture, then cheese sauce.
Should make 2 layers, then top with Cheddar cheese.

title: aunt crease's buttermilk pies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add flour and eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix well and dip apples.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and shortening together until fluffy.
Add milk and keep mixer at low speed.
Add the flour, a little at a time.
Add the vanilla last and beat this icing for at least 10 minutes once all the ingredients are in place.
Does not need to be refrigerated to store.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen or fryers.
Remove bone and save broth.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery in oleo.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts, pimentos, soups, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 9 x 13 inch pyrex dish, pour a little olive oil. Dredge chicken in olive oil. Pour chopped vegetables over chicken. Sprinkle salt, pepper, oregano and basil over chicken. Mix vinegar and tomatoes together and pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
In large bowl, toss bacon with the potatoes and onions; set aside.
In drippings, combine flour and sugar.
Combine water, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cream.
Pour over potato mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chuck wagon black-eyes
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add other ingredients and let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: rosemary walnuts
directions: Melt margarine or butter in large saucepan.
Remove from heat and add seasonings.
Add walnuts and toss gently, but well.
Place walnuts in a shallow pan in one layer.
Bake at 325° until brown, about 10 to 12 minutes, shaking occasionally.
Serve warm.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients 30 minutes with pan covered.
After mixture begins to boil, add chicken soup, water (to rinse out cans) and Velveeta cheese.
Cook until all cheese is melted.
Serve with Mexican cornbread.

title: tollhouse pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter. Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chilies, chicken broth or water, chili powder and cumin. Microwave on High 4 minutes or until heated through.
Stir in cream cheese; stir until melted.
Spoon 1/3 cup into a tortilla and roll up.
Place, seam side down, in glass pan.
Melt Velveeta in milk.
Pour over tortillas.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine in saucepan and heat slowly until cheese is melted and is well blended.
Serve warm with dip size Fritos or Doritos.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Cook at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and put in a food processor (after cleaned).
Chop.
Set aside.
Put shrimp in a food processor and chop with the onion.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Line a casserole dish with Fritos. Put a layer of chicken over the Fritos.
Make a sauce of milk, tomatoes, chicken soup, mushroom soup, onions and chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Place grated cheese on top of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be frozen prior to baking.

title: snickers cheese cake
directions: Freeze Snickers and then beat them to crush.
Mix everything and pour into crust. If too thick, add a little milk. Cool and then serve.

title: chocolate waffles with strawberry cream
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar and cocoa in a large bowl. Combine egg yolk, buttermilk and butter.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat egg white at room temperature until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold into batter.
Bake in preheated, oiled waffle iron.

title: filipino banana fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add milk and water, then egg.
Mix until smooth.
Peel bananas and cut at a slant.
Roll bananas in flour and coat in batter.
Fry in hot oil, turning to brown both sides evenly.
Drain.

title: pinch donuts
directions: Pinch off pieces of bread and drop in Bundt pan.
On top of stove in saucepan (medium), melt margarine and then add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a low boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over bread and bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Turn donuts out on foil on a cookie sheet; the pudding mixture will run, so be careful.

title: easy baked beans and bacon
directions: Saute bacon and onions, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: creamy corn plus
directions: With sharp knife, cut tips of corn off the cob. With back of knife, scrape off remaining pulp and juice. In a 10-inch skillet, stir in margarine until melted. Add squash, corn, salt and pepper; cover. Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Reduce thin liquid in the skillet by cooking a few minutes on high, stirring briskly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wesson jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion until soft in hot Wesson oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: In an electric skillet or large skillet with cover, place butter and oil and heat until butter melts.
Add onion and saut until transparent.
Add mushroom crowns to saut.
Mix carefully until mushrooms are well coated.
Cover.
Cook at low heat 2 minutes.
Add herbs, crushing between hands.
Add garlic salt and salt; mix carefully but thoroughly.
Pour lime juice and sherry over all.
Cook covered on moderate heat until mushrooms are tender.
Uncover and continue cooking until mushrooms have absorbed the liquid (approximately 1/2 hour).
Remove from heat.
Let sit at least two hours at room temperature.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a shallow pan which has been greased with margarine or oil.
Melt margarine; stir in pineapple, mustard, honey and sherry.
Spoon pineapple mixture over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes, until tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chicken on top of green beans.
Mix together soup and mayonnaise and spread over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and place cheese on top of casserole.
Leave in oven until cheese melts.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill. Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brown meat in a skillet; drain on paper towel.
Roll biscuits on floured board or waxed paper until they form 4-inch circles.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil; grease lightly with shortening.
Place rolled biscuits on cookie sheet.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Spread the sauce mixture on the crusts.
Sprinkle on the drained meat.
Next, sprinkle on the grated cheese.
Top with oregano.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts and starts to brown.
(Other ingredients may be added, also.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the oleo, vanilla, peanut butter and sugar by hand. Form this substance into balls.
Pat to flatten.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Stick balls with a toothpick and dip into melted chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: sloppy joes(can be doubled)
directions: Cook beef and onions on high 4 to 6 minutes or until meat is cooked.
Drain meat to remove fat.
Mix remaining ingredients. Cook on high 5 to 7 more minutes.
If you make a double batch, make it with one can cream of chicken soup and one can cream of celery soup, then just double everything else.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Mix crumbs with grated cheese. Add garlic salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Dip lightly salted chicken in melted butter. Roll in crumbs. Place on baking sheet, fat side of breast up.
Be sure top of breast is covered with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sunshine pickles
directions: Wash cukes.
Put dill on the bottom of a large jar; add cukes and put dill in the middle and on top, also.
Cut garlic and place on the layers.
Add alum.
Mix water, vinegar and salt and pour over pickles.
Let them sit in direct sunlight for 2 days or 3 if you like them more sour.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: barbecue chicken(crock-pot)
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients.
Put chicken in bottom of crock-pot. Pour mixture over chicken.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in pie filling and nuts.
Add cream cheese to milk.
Add Cool Whip if you like.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt
peanut
butter,
margarine and chocolate chips in large saucepan over medium
heat.
Pour
cereal
into
a	very large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal and mix gently using a spatula.
Mix until cereal is well coated.	Let cereal cool.
Add powdered sugar a
little
at a time until cereal is coated.
This gives the
cereal
the
appearance	of dog food, hence the name.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together.
Add remaining ingredients to milk mixture.
Pour into pie shells and chill overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix berries and sugar and let set for a couple of hours. Dissolve the Jell-O in hot water and refrigerate until almost set. Mix the last 4 ingredients together and add to Jell-O and berries.
Mix well and chill.

title: artichokes rhoadesian
directions: Rinse artichokes thoroughly in running cold water; drain on paper towel.
Snap off small bottom leaves, slice off stem and immediately dip into 3 tablespoons of lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Trim the thorn tip off each leaf (about 1/2-inch) and slice off top of artichoke to eliminate thorns on leaves not easily trimmed.
Dip and roll in lemon juice.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes and gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together the dry ingredients; fold into pumpkin.
Put into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto 10x sugar-sprinkled towel.
Roll up from narrow end and cool.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Mix first five ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch (Pyrex) buttered dish.
Place skinless, boneless chicken breasts in dish after patting with butter, salt and pepper.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bake chicken breast; set aside. Mix broth, soups, Ro-Tel and water. Layer tortilla chips, chicken (cut up), soup mix and Mexican cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll out and cut cookies on a floured surface; thick if you like soft cookies, thin if you like crisp cookies.
Sprinkle sugar on top if you like.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are great for decorating with "decorator icing".

title: potato and garlic
directions: Boil garlic and potatoes.
Mash; add the rest of ingredients and serve.

title: pierogi lasagna
directions: Saute onions and butter in sauce pan until just tender.
Do not brown them.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Cook potatoes, mash and mix with cheese while potatoes are warm.
Pour enough onion mixture to cover the bottom of a 9x13 in pan.
Put layer of noodles.
Spread layer of potato and cheese over noodles. Drizzle onion and butter over potatoes.
Repeat process until you have 4 or 5 layers.
Top layer should be potato and cheese. Drizzle with remaining onions and top with 1/4 cup longhorn cheese. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp marcella
directions: In
a
large
saucepan over moderately high heat, saute shrimp in
1 stick butter until they turn pink.
Stir in green onions and mushrooms.
Saute about 7 minutes or until vegetables
are soft.
With
slotted spoon, transfer shrimp to bowl and keep warm.

title: walnut broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli as directed.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Spoon broccoli into prepared casserole.
In small saucepan combine 1/2 cup butter, flour and bouillon; mix well, gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Pour over broccoli.
In small pan, combine water and 1/3 cup butter, add herb stuffing and walnuts.
Spoon stuffing mixture over broccoli.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: red beet cake
directions: Boil beets and put through blender.
Mix everything together. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: bread dressing for 15 to 20 pound bird
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Cook celery and onion in butter. Mix all ingredients and seasonings to taste.
Dressing should be quite moist.
Stuff into bird or bake in large casserole for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: twenty minute chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together. Combine butter, Crisco, cocoa and water. Bring to a boil. Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli.
Boil sugar and vinegar to dissolve; set aside to cool.
Add pimentos to cauliflower and broccoli.
Add cooled sugar and vinegar, mayonnaise and salt.
Stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: eggplant and roasted red pepper pizza
directions: Salt eggplant cubes; let drain 30 minutes.
Pat dry.
In a microwave-safe bowl, combine eggplant and olive oil.
Stir. Vent.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Add peppers and onion. Microwave another 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Press out pizza dough on greased cookie sheet.
Drizzle with olive oil. Spread eggplant mixture evenly on pizza dough.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot puffs
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in a small portion of boiling salted water for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.
Mash carrots; let cool.
Combine a cup mashed carrots and the next 7 ingredients; stir well.
Heat 1 inch of oil in a large skillet to 325°.
Drop carrot mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil; cook until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: grandma barb's peachy peach pie
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into sugar and flour like you would a pie crust.
Put half of the mixture in bottom of unbaked crust. Place sliced peaches over crumb mixture. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over peaches. Pour cream over.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per directions on box and put into a greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together (mixes easier if heated).
Pour over broccoli.
Top with 1 1/2 pkg. of Pepperidge Farm Dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Crumble cake for first layer in large bowl.
Mix pudding as directed and pour over cake.
Crumble second layer of cake over pudding.
Spread drained pineapple over cake. Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pie filling.
Put cherries on Cool Whip, also nuts if wanted.

title: butterscotch cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, melt butterscotch morsels and butter.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts. Press half of the mixture firmly onto the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve the rest for topping.
Blend cream cheese until smooth.
Add condensed milk and blend well.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Pour over crumb mixture and top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted in the middle.
Chill before cutting into squares.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 18.
Garnish with extra cookies.

title: cold artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop up.
Add Ranch dressing package to mayonnaise.
Fold in artichokes.
Chill and serve.

title: caramel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a small saucepan. Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Serve with apple slices.

title: hash brown casserole(a man-pleaser)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the 1/4 cup of melted margarine and bread crumbs. Put into a well-greased casserole dish; mix margarine and bread crumbs. Sprinkle top with crumbs and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour and Parmesan cheese in plastic bag.
Shake a few potatoes in bag at a time and put in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
With spatula, turn potatoes over and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: orange ritz salad
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some to sprinkle on top.
Mix thawed orange juice with condensed milk.
Add thawed Cool Whip; mix well.
Add well drained oranges.
Spread in crust; sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Best made a day ahead.

title: low calorie strawberry breakfast spread
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over orange juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Heat over low heat until gelatin is dissolved and mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and stir into strawberries.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend. Refrigerate until firm, 3 to 4 hours.

title: kids pizza
directions: Spray cookie sheet.
Press biscuits onto sheet.
Add sauce. Add other ingredients.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: ranch beans
directions: Saute bacon, onion and green pepper.
Add meat and brown. Stir in ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and a few sprinkles of liquid smoke.
Add beans.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: mexican spoon bread(yield:  8 to 10 servings)
directions: Mix together corn, milk, oil and eggs.
Add corn meal, baking soda and salt.
Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan or similar size baking dish.
Sprinkle with green chiles and half of the cheese.
Spread remaining batter on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Cool just enough to set, 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into serving size squares or spoon out.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Stir all ingredients together in punch bowl. Add ice ring with maraschino cherries and crushed pineapple.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix strawberries and glaze; refrigerate.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk; set aside.
In an oblong dish (9 x 12 x 2-inch), layer the vanilla wafers.
Pour the cream cheese mixture on top of the wafers.
Spread the strawberry mixture on top of the cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours prior to serving.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni per directions on the box.
Then stir in soup and Cheez Whiz.
In a baking dish, place the broccoli on the bottom then pour mixture over the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves a family of 6.

title: macaroni-tomato casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in water with salt, until tender, stirring often. Dice baking meat and onion.
Put butter in a thick skillet and heat, add hamburger meat, baking meat and onion.
Cook until brown, stirring all the time you are cooking it.
(May need to add a spoon or two of baking grease while browning it.)
Put tomato soup in large mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Mix in the water from the cooked macaroni until you can mix it well.
Put all into buttered cooking dish.
Grate 4 tablespoons cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots.
Drain and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add carrots.
Chill several hours or overnight. Keeps for one week in refrigerator.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix and stir while cooking the sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla.
Be sure the pie crust and filling are cold before you pour into pie crust.
Top with whipping cream, Cool Whip or meringue. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in water.
Cool, then add other ingredients. Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
This salad is served with meat.

title: fiesta appetizer
directions: In a bowl, mash the avocados with lemon juice.
Spread mixture evenly in the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Spread sour cream evenly over avocado mixture.
Spoon sauce over sour cream layer. Sprinkle green onions over salsa sauce.
Top with cheese.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Serve with chips.

title: virgin pina colada
directions: Combine coconut milk and juice.
Mix well with blender.
Add crushed ice.
Place pieces of pineapple and cherries on toothpick as garnish and put over top of each glass.
Serves 20.

title: walnut creams
directions: Use wooden spoon for stirring.
Mix sugar, milk, syrup and salt well before cooking.
Cook over very low heat until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cool water.
Set aside to cool until lukewarm (do not stir).
When candy thickens, stir in vanilla and nuts and stir until candy turns creamy in color and holds shape when dropped onto wax paper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 pan in 350-degree oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill.
Serve with Fritos.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Layer shredded lettuce (shaved very fine), grated carrots, chopped celery and peas in a bowl.
Top with small dabs of salad dressing and sprinkle with sugar.
Repeat layers for desired quantity.
Over top layer, sprinkle crisp crumbled bacon.
Do not toss.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Pour soup and cheese over vegetables.
Cover with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: triple herb steak rub
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Rub on steak and broil to desired doneness.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir together in a 3-quart saucepan the sugar, margarine, salt and milk.
Boil until soft ball stage, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter, stirring until mixture begins to harden.
Pour into greased dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with stuffing and 1/2 cup of chicken broth. Place 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of baking casserole dish.

title: pot roast
directions: Put oil in heavy pan; brown roast rubbed with meat tenderizer. Add all other ingredients; cover with water.
Cook slow for 5 hours.
Can add more vegetables if family is larger than 4.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add the beaten egg and then the molasses and milk.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Mix again.
Put in loaf pans and let rise for about 20 minutes. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: pepper rice
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet; add mushrooms, garlic, green pepper, onion and rice.
Stir over heat until rice turns yellow. Add broth and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown sausage, crumble and drain.
Grate cheese, add to sausage with seasonings.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on bread slices and spoon sauce on top of this.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Freezes well.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
After frozen, put in freezer bags.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Over medium heat, saute onion in oil until soft. Add mushrooms; cook about 4 minutes until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer, covered, about 1 hour or until barley is tender.
Remove bay leaf. Serves 4.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in a little oleo.
Mix together with the first mixture.
Crumble 1 tube of Ritz crackers.
Pour melted oleo over crackers.
Mix and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: curried cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender-crisp and set aside in a large casserole dish. Combine milk, soup, mayonnaise, cheese and curry powder.
Pour over cauliflower.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: dream cookies
directions: Put the first 6 ingredients in a large pan and bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add the remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper and let cool.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook head of broccoli, then cook chicken until done. In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients. In 9 x 15 casserole dish, place broccoli then chicken. Then pour in the remaining ingredients. Spread out and cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump can of cherry pie filling in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Dump pineapple with juice in next.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top. Cut butter into pats and put on top of cake mix.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: summer squash scramble
directions: Combine onion, garlic and oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet. Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add squash, basil and salt.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until squash is tender.
Stir constantly.
Stir in tomatoes.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops; remove excess grease.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; pour over chops and cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: shrimp pasta medley
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet on medium heat. Add garlic; cook and stir until lightly browned. Stir in shrimp, half and half, pea pods, bell pepper, water and crushed red pepper. Simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink. Pour sauce mixture over hot linguine. Sprinkle with 3/4 c. of cheese; toss to coat. Serve with remaining 1/4 c. cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix in order given; knead well.
Let rise 1 hour, working down every 15 minutes.
Shape into 6 loaves; let rise again and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together margarine, cocoa and vanilla.
Add peanut butter (mix well and remove from heat).
Add confectioners sugar (will get very stiff; may need to use hands to mix).
Spread onto cookie sheet or shallow baking pan, cover with wax paper and use rolling pin to smooth.
Chill at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and mix with pretzels, sugar and pecans.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Beat cream cheese, nondairy topping and powdered sugar. Spread on top of pretzel mixture.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add strawberries and stir until gelatin begins to thicken.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate about 2 hours.
Top with whipped topping.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meat pie
directions: Fry onion in butter until golden.
Put meat in pan and cook (do not fry) until white.
Pour off if excess fat; must have some. Put bread crumbs and spices in and mix together.
Divide into 2 pie crusts and cover with crust.
Bake 1/2 hour in 400° oven.
Can be made and frozen for future use.
Just head in 350° oven until warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings per pie.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix in large punch bowl.
Add ice mold.
Ice mold should have limes, lemons (sliced) and strawberries in it.
Add a little yellow or green food coloring to mold.
Looks great in punch bowl.

title: honey-baked barbecued chicken
directions: Place cut up pieces of chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix barbecue sauce ingredients in order given and pour over chicken pieces. Turn pieces to coat entire chicken.
Bake in a 325° oven approximately 70 minutes. Turn pieces once or twice during baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
For added color, add a few drops of red food color.
Beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Whip cream.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour filling into crust; freeze until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: anniversary punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine the lemonade, water and pineapple juice, mixing well.
Add the chilled ginger ale.

title: fresh italian orange dessert
directions: Cut a slice from the top of each orange; cut off peel in strips from top to bottom, cutting deep enough to remove white membrane.
Cut oranges into crosswise slices.
In a small bowl, mix Ricotta, sugar and liqueur.
To serve, arrange orange slices on platter and top with Ricotta mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: junkyard salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.

title: delicious apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and nutmeg together.
Add chopped apples to sugar mixture and beat well.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down evenly.
Melt 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips and spread on top of peanut butter mix.
Cut in squares.
Cool in fridge.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Use your own favorite recipe for a 2-crust pie.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Place butter in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Microwave at High 45 seconds or until melted.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic; toss gently.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Beat eggs and add all ingredients.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish, lightly oiled.
Bake at 350° for 28 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into finger pieces.

title: zesty angel hair pasta
directions: *Do not use reduced calorie dressing.

title: coffee liqueur clouds
directions: In a blender, thoroughly mix Ricotta cheese, whipped lite cream, cinnamon, sugar and coffee liqueur.
Blend until smooth. Divide mandarin oranges evenly into fine dessert dishes and top each with 1/2 cup of cheese mixture.
Garnish with cinnamon.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding and add milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer whole crackers and pudding mixture in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat layers, ending with crackers.
Spread chocolate icing over crackers and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Stir in Seven-Up.
Chill.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown
hamburg,
onions,
garlic,
oregano,
basil
and Accent.
Make sure this is fried good.
(Beef stew meat may be used in place of
hamburg.
Cook
until
done and save broth.) Add to tomato juice.
Cook
each vegetable separately;
do not cook vegetables and noodles too soft.
Add all of water except celery water.
Add bouillon cubes.
Taste for salt and pepper. Mix all together and can.
Cold pack 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked chicken in onion soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flour chicken parts.
Arrange in shallow baking pan, skin side down.
Make soup per package directions, except use only 3 cups water.
Add butter to hot soup and stir to dissolve.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 45 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: pork picnic ham
directions: Wash meat.
Do not use salt.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Place celery, onion and pepper on ham.
Wrap enough foil to close edges.
Bake in slow oven at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Pork should be well done.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate biscuits into 20 pieces. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuits into melted butter, then roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits in a single layer, overlapping slightly if necessary, in deep baking dish. Peel, core and slice apples.
Cut apple slice in half. Place an apple slice between each biscuit and around outer edge of dish. Mix nuts and raisins with remaining cinnamon/sugar mixture and sprinkle over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Place spices in cheesecloth and drop in.
Let simmer, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with 1/4 cup butter.
Line your pan with broccoli, cabbage and onion.
Mix together soup and mayo.
Pour over vegetables.
Put on stuffing.
Top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown chops.
Saute pepper and onion.
Add tomatoes and chops; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add rice; cook until rice is done.

title: salsa chicken and cheese grill
directions: Top 1 bread slice with 1 cheese slice, salsa, chicken, second cheese slice and top with second bread slice.
Spread sandwich on both sides with margarine.
Grill over low heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: turkey and schnitzel dijon
directions: Mix egg whites, water, mustard, salt and pepper in a shallow dish with a fork until blended.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cream butter until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, then vanilla, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sour cream.
Gradually add flour until all is incorporated.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 1/2-inch apart on prepared sheets.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool 1 to 2 minutes on sheets, then remove to wire racks.
Ice or decorate as desired.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, blend together cheese and butter.
Work in flour and pepper evenly until it forms a soft dough. Work in Rice Krispies until evenly mixed.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Press flat on palm of hand.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Prick tops with toothpick.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 50 to 60.

title: mattie's company dish(150 years old)
directions: Keep eggs and cream separate.
To the egg mixture, gradually add a pound of powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Whip in the cream.
Slice 3 large bananas and 1 pineapple; cut into cubes. Beat these into cream and chill.
When cold, serve them in pretty glasses.

title: smoking bishop
directions: Stud the orange with the cloves and bake it in a 350° oven until the skin has browned, about 40 minutes.

Cut the orange in quarters and place in a heavy saucepan with the sugar and water. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring to dissolve the sugar, then reduce the heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.
Add the wine and heat until the mixture is "smoking" hot.
Pour into a heated punch bowl and serve.

title: banana supreme pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla until thick. Layer sliced bananas on bottom of crust.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Top with more sliced bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Crust can be graham cracker crust or use vanilla wafers in bottom and sides of 8-inch square dish.

title: peppermint ice cream pie
directions: First Layer:
Finely grind wafers in blender.
Thoroughly blend butter and sugar (by hand).
Press mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 3 minutes or less. Cool before filling.

title: fluffy cake doughnuts
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add melted shortening, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix quickly.
Brush doughnut maker with light coating of vegetable oil and fill with batter.
Hold doughnut maker over oil at surface and release ring of batter onto surface.
Deep fat fry at 375° (medium) for approximately 1 minute on each side, turning to brown evenly. Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
When done, cover doughnuts with sugar or cinnamon sugar, or your favorite topping.

title: fried trout
directions: Preheat frying pan and shortening.
Roll fish in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Place fish in pan on medium heat and fry, turning as needed until brown and well done.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, including nuts, in a large bowl; stir well to blend.

title: brownies no. 1
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure, add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Add butter to chocolate and blend.
Combine sugar and eggs.
Add the chocolate mixture; beat in thoroughly.
Then add flour, vanilla and nuts.

title: crescent roll
directions: Mix until smooth the sugar and shortening.
Add salt and stir in 3/4 cup warm milk.
Crumble yeast into mixture.
Beat in flour with spoon.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Roll out in circle and spread with melted butter.
Cut like pie and roll up!
Place on baking sheet and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 425°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put sugar, flour and salt in large mixing bowl and set aside. In saucepan, put butter, oil, water and cocoa.
Bring to boil. Pour over dry ingredients and add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Pour in sheet pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lisa's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, reserving 1/2 cup crushed pecans. Shape into a ball.
Roll ball in the reserved 1/2 cup pecans. Chill.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender. Cook noodles 6 to 8 minutes and peas until tender.
Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1 cup of cheese for top.
Use a lot of celery salt.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
May be frozen for later use.
Do not cook before freezing. Do not cover while baking.

title: holiday mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water.
Spoon into crust and gently spread to cover bottom.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar, milk and peppermint extract.
Fold in whipped topping. Divide mixture in half and stir food coloring into one half, until even color.
Fill pie crust with alternate dollops of green and white mixture.
Smooth top of pie with spatula.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave oven and pour evenly over broccoli.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Cut ice cream into 6 pieces; add hot liquid.
Stir until melted.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill to set.
Top with whip cream.

title: sicilian orange salad
directions: Mix everything together, except for the oranges and olives. Arrange the orange slices on a platter.
Add the olives and salad dressing.

title: apple-carrot muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients, then add liquids.
Stir until moist.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done, yields about 2 dozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onions, tomatoes and dry Italian dressing mix.
Cook and cool spaghetti (cook amount you want); add to cucumber mixture.
Then add 1 bottle of Seven Seas Italian dressing.
Toss well.
Chill 2 hours or overnight before serving.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 cup butter.
Add celery and saute.
Add shrimp and mushrooms and saute until shrimp are pink.
Add crabmeat, parsley, half and half, Worcestershire sauce, bread crumbs and Creole seasoning.
Slit skin of flounder on dark side, lengthwise down center.
Run knife between skin and fish, being careful not to puncture skin.
Fill pockets with stuffing.
Place in buttered shallow baking dish.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter; add oil and lemon juice.
Brush over fish.
Bake 25 minutes.
Baste occasionally with Italian dressing.
Serve with lemon wedges. Serves 4 adults.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Soak in salted water for a couple of hours.
Combine remaining ingredients in large iron skillet, and add drained shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; stir every 10 minutes.
Serve over angel hair pasta or thin spaghetti noodles. Serves 6.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk or buttermilk and shortening.
Beat with rotary or electric beater until just smooth, about 1 minute (do not overbeat). Pour batter into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oriental stir-fry chicken
directions: Put cornstarch, salt, garlic and sherry in bowl; stir well. Add chicken that has been cut in 3/4-inch pieces (bite size) and mix well.
Let sit for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Stir again to make sure all pieces are separated.
Add 1/4 cup of oil to skillet and when hot, add chicken stirring quickly about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vegetables and sprinkle liberally with soy sauce.
Continue stirring about 3 to 5 minutes.
Vegetables should be medium crisp, not mushy. Serve with a bowl of fluffy white rice.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs (not beaten).
Add rest of ingredients.
Form into a long roll and wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Roll dough into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread pork sausage over dough, leaving 1/2 inch margin on all sides (may add grated cheese, if desired).
Carefully roll dough lengthwise, jelly roll fashion.
Pinch seam and ends to seal.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices. Arrange 1 inch apart on baking sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: french pancakes
directions: Mix all and grill as pancakes on grill with melted oleo. Serve with syrup.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, onions, peppers, pimento, salt and water together. Mix and pack ice over mixture.
Let set for 1 1/2 hours; drain. Bring the sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed to a boil. Add to squash mixture and let come to a boil.
Place in jars and seal.
Great with vegetables.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; add Karo syrup and eggs.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shred cheese; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Add milk all at once; cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Add shredded cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook until cheese melts. Remove from heat.
Add potatoes and onions to cheese sauce.
Cook with semi-boneless ham for 12 hours in a crock-pot.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together. In large Pyrex dish, spread bean dip to the edge. Then layer guacamole, sour cream, tomatoes, onions, cheese and olives. Serve with corn chips.

title: vida's mock ravioli(a vegetarian dish)
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix together spinach, olive oil, bread crumbs, parsley, cheese, garlic, salt and sage.
In a baking dish or casserole, place a layer of noodles on bottom.
Top with a layer of spinach mixture and cover with a layer of spaghetti sauce.
Repeat until dish is full with last layer of lasagna topped with sauce.
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: principal's coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch well to prevent lumps.
Add 1 cup milk, stirring constantly (dissolve all lumps).
Add other cup of milk.
(Use a very heavy saucepan.)
Cook over moderately hot eye until mixture begins to thicken.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Stir and cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well. Beat egg whites until peaks form. Add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Arrange on top of pie and bake until light brown.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt in an ungreased 9 x 12-inch bake pan.
Make 3 holes and put vanilla, vinegar and oil in the holes.
Over all, put the cold water and stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it tests done with toothpick.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt oleo; add coconut and chopped pecans.
Brown lightly on top of stove, stirring until brown.
Set aside and cool completely.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix cream of chicken soup, chili beans and Ro-Tel together.
Add meat.
Spread crushed Doritos on bottom of pan and cover with the mix.
Sprinkle cheese and then repeat with another layer of the mixture.
End with grated cheese on top.
Cook at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and crispy pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in 3 cups lime and 2 gallons water for 24 hours.
Rinse.
Soak in 2 gallons water for 24 hours.
Soak in alum and 2 gallons water for 24 hours.
Soak in ground ginger and 2 gallons water for 16 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl and place in microwave oven.
Microwave on Medium-high for 1 minute. Mix together.
Serve with cut up vegetables, crackers or bread.

title: cool strawberry cake
directions: Poke
holes in cake.
Mix jello and water.
Pour over cake. Refrigerate cake.
Drizzle strawberry syrup over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place sliced strawberries on top. Keep in refrigerator.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Dice the potatoes and cook with onion, celery and water, until tender.
Do not drain.
Mash the mixture with seasonings, add butter, cheese and milk.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and salt.
Heat on medium-high until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Enjoy over hot biscuits or muffins.

title: christmas bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts, raisins and cherries.
Mix well.
Add egg, butter and bananas.
Stir.
Place in a well-greased loaf pan and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake next day for 1 hour at 350°.

title: morgan's grandmama ruth's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese zucchini crisps(good!)
directions: Combine cornflake crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Place in dish.
Dip zucchini strips in butter, then shake in crumbs to coat.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: 3 ingredient fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in top of double boiler. Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate to chill.
Cut into 1-inch pieces. Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: gretchen's noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add margarine and stir until melted. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Add noodles to mix.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a medium oven until bubbly.

title: apple buckle dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice apples thin, wash and fill dish half full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and a little sugar.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Stir 1/4 cup of tomato soup into the beaten egg. Mix together with the rice, parsley flakes, onion, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 20 (1-inch) meatballs. Place meatballs into a skillet.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until done; skin and debone.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Heat soups together.
Begin by layering broccoli, chicken (torn into pieces), cheese and soup.
Into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, mix melted oleo and bread crumbs together.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, rinse and slice thin.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish as follows:
one layer potatoes, margarine (pats scattered), flour, salt and pepper.
Continue layering and add another layer of potatoes on top.
Add milk (add only enough milk to almost cover all the layers).
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes. Turn potatoes twice during baking.
Add cheese to the top for the last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: (perfect) cornbread
directions: Mix flour with sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: marinated grilled turkey
directions: Score turkey breasts.
Place in a large plastic container. Pour beer over top.
Generously sprinkle with hickory salt.
Let turkey marinate for 3 to 4 hours at room temperature.
Place on grill and lightly sprinkle with additional hickory salt.
Grill 20 to 25 minutes or until turkey is browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool about 15 minutes, then remove from pan onto rack and cool completely.

title: fried pie
directions: Place apples in cold water in a large sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and then reduce to medium low heat.
Simmer until tender - approximately 20 minutes.
Add sugar, cinnamon, and/or nutmeg and mix well.

Potato masher can be used to mash apples slightly. Place 2 tablespoons apples in center of 6-inch rounds of pie crust. Moisten edges with water, fold and press edges firmly with fork. Fry in melted shortening until brown.
Shortening can be decreased in pie crust for fried pies.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries well.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler, cool slightly.
Make a fondant with the powdered sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla.
This should be of a stiff dough consistency that can be handled.
If too stiff, add a little of the cherry juice.
If too thin, add more powdered sugar.
Take a small amount of dough and flatten to about the size of a half dollar, wrap around cherry.
Use a toothpick as holder and dip in melted chocolate and paraffin.
Place on waxed paper and let set 2 hours before handling.

title: taco dip
directions: Dice separately the onions, tomatoes and green onion.
Mash avocado and mix in lemon juice.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
In your favorite dish, layer from bottom up:
refried beans, avocado/lemon juice, mixed sour cream/mayonnaise/taco seasoning mix, sliced black olives, tomato bits, shredded Colby cheese and green onions.
Serve with favorite corn chips.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil rice; drain.
Cook peas and carrots in saucepan.
Spray frying pan with cooking spray.
Put rice, peas and carrots in pan. Mix water, soy sauce and rice mix in cup.
Pour in pan.
Mix together; simmer.
Push rice to one side of pan and scramble eggs; mix together.

title: dirt
directions: In a large bowl, mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Add milk and instant pudding.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grind Oreos in blender until fine.
Set aside.
In a large bowl or sand bucket, layer cookie crumbs, pudding mix, ending with cookie crumbs on top.
Chill several hours.
For a humorous touch, top with gummy worms.

title: black bean tortilla pie
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper until done.
Add beans, salsa, jalapenos, chili powder and cayenne.
Simmer 10 minutes. Put 1/2 cup of mixture into bottom pie crust, sprinkle with cheese and top with tortilla.
Repeat, layering twice.
Top with top pie crust; cut slits in top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 30 minutes or until tender.
Let cool; peel and slice.
Place potatoes in a serving bowl.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove, drain and crumble and add to potatoes.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Stir flour into fat in skillet.
Gradually add vinegar and water, stirring constantly, to make a smooth mixture. Add sugar, onion and celery.
Cook until sauce is hot and slightly thickened.
Pour hot sauce over potatoes and bacon.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve hot.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour dressing over and stir well. Eat with tortilla chips.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thick.
Roll them in egg, salt and pepper, then in bread crumbs.
Heat oil to very hot. Brown on both sides.
Remove to shallow baking dish.
Stir in tomato sauce and spices to the oil they were browned in.
Boil for a minute, then simmer 10 minutes until thick.
Add oleo.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Put Mozzarella on top.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: frosted fruit mold(7-up jelly salad)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cook.
Add carbonated beverage.
Chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Fold drained pineapple and banana into jello mixture. Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine sugar and flour in pan.
Stir in reserved pineapple syrup and the egg.
Cook and stir until thickened; chill.
Whip cream; fold into egg mixture.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with cheese and cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add and mix well.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian sausage pie
directions: Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Romano cheeses.
Stir in eggs, cooked sausage, salami, oregano, basil, garlic and parsley.
Place crust on a lightly oiled pie dish.
Put all ingredients in pan on crust.
Put top crust on, fit over filling, sealing edges.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden. Cool about 10 minutes before serving.

title: homemade soup
directions: Mix ingredients into a large pot.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: mom's mushroom meat loaf
directions: Drain chopped mushrooms and mix mushroom juice with milk to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine in mixing bowl:
egg, Worcestershire, seasoning, liquid and bread.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in meat and mushrooms.
Press into loaf pan or shape into loaf and place in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar, and vanilla. Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 400 degrees 10-12 minutes. Cool to luke warm. Roll in powdered sugar and store in powdered sugar.

title: butterscotch breakfast rolls
directions: Place 20 to 24 frozen rolls in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry pudding, brown sugar, melted oleo and chopped nuts over them.
Cover with foil.
Place in cool oven overnight.
In the morning bake about 20 minutes at 375°.

title: ethan's orange juice shake
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a blender; process at high speed.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, blending until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: honey toast
directions: You have to have pancake mix.
You have to have 1 or 2 eggs if you want.
Daddy usually puts 1 egg.
Then you stir it.
Then if it's really mushy, you get buttermilk in it.
You stir it again. Add more if it needs it.
You pour it in the pan.
Wait until all the bubbles go out.
Then you flip them.
Then you eat it with syrup.

title: mary jewel's dip
directions: Make this in a blender.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven according to biscuit directions.
Cut each biscuit in half and wrap around the sausages, one at a time. Place on cookie sheet; bake according to biscuit directions.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic in a skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine the flour, chili powder, salt and cumin. Gradually stir in hot water.
Combine with meat mixture.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Add kidney beans and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: carol's macaroni salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions, drain and cool.
Mix Miracle Whip and Good Seasons dressing together.
Add this mixture to noodles.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss well to coat vegetables.

title: vitamin salad
directions: Let Jell-O jell.
Add lemon juice to bananas, carrots, celery (cut fine) and pineapple.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and juices.
Layer, starting with bananas, peaches and pineapple.
Pour mixture over fruit.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Brown together in large frying pan: 1 or more pounds ground beef, 1 cup chopped celery and 2 medium onions.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 1/2 cups water, added to soup cans.
Add 1/4 cup soy sauce or ostroms sauce or 1 can mushrooms.
Add 1/2 cup uncooked rice.
Mix all together well.
Pour into large casserole and bake (325°) for 1/2 hour, uncovered, and 1/2 hour, covered.
Sprinkle top with Chinese noodles.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring vigorously.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and a piece of butter.
Beat with a rotary beater for 1 minute and serve hot or cold.
Store in refrigerator and reheat as needed.

title: rice-artichoke salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni by package directions, omitting the butter. Cool.
Add onions, peppers, olives and artichokes.
Mix artichoke liquid with mayonnaise and curry powder; toss with salad lightly. Chill overnight.

title: red bean toss
directions: Drain kidney beans and shred cheese.
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Blend seasonings with mayonnaise and add to bean mixture.
Toss lightly.
Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cherry surprise cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl. Separate eggs; beat whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat yolks in a small bowl with lemon juice until thick. Add 1/4 cup sugar gradually.
Beat until thick and fluffy.
Fold flour mixture into yolks.
Fold yolks into whites.
Spread in a 10-inch plate that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: goulash(diet)
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch square pieces.
Heat oil and add the meat.
When meat is browned on all sides, add the chopped onion and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add salt, paprika, pepper, tomato paste, caraway seed and flour or cornstarch.
Stir thoroughly; add water and simmer very slowly for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in yogurt.
Remove from heat immediately.
Serves 6. Exchange per serving:
3 meats, 1/2 milk and 1 fat.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Cover broccoli and mushrooms with dressing and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add 1 can pitted ripe olives and 1 sliced red onion.
Can be served on lettuce if desired.
Serves 6.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Do not beat, just stir until blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake in 350° oven.
This is delicious.
Can be frozen for several months.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to butter and sugar with milk and vanilla.
Make sauce for dumplings.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O; refrigerate until just barely set.
It should be just starting to set, don't let it set.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix well sugar, salt and spices.
Combine with pumpkin, brown sugar and eggs, scalded evaporated milk and water.
Stir until evenly blended.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with pecan topping. Return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: goop
directions: Add water to cornstarch until mixture forms a paste-like consistency.
(Important:
When mixture is handled, it should melt through your fingers.)
Add food coloring, if desired.
Pour mixture into a sensory bin and enjoy!
This is a wonderful tacticle experience for children and is not made to take home.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: oyster loaf
directions: Cut the crust from the loaf entirely.
Cut a fairly thick slice from the top of the loaf and save it for a lid.
Hollow out the crumbs from the loaf.
Spread it thickly inside with softened butter and toast the loaf until it is an even golden brown inside and out, also the lid.

title: sugar-free barbecue sauce(diabetic; 1 tablespoon = free)
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Store in jar in the refrigerator.

title: fried squirrel(modern)
directions: Cut squirrels in half.
Dredge squirrels with mixture of salt, pepper and flour.
Fry in hot lard in heavy skillet until golden. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of lard.
Boil 1 1/2 cups of water and pour over squirrel.
Cover and cook over a low heat for 1 hour.

title: peaches flambe
directions: In chafing dish or saucepan, combine jam, sugar and water. Simmer over low heat until syrupy, about 5 minutes.
Add peaches; cook over low heat until almost tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Heat brandy just until warm; pour slowly over peaches and ignite immediately.
Do not stir.
Spoon sauce and peaches over ice cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet noodle pudding(grits kugel)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat remaining ingredients, except pineapple and raisins.
Pour into well buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until top is golden.

title: barbecued brisket(this is really great!!!)
directions: Rub 2 tablespoons liquid smoke over well trimmed brisket and refrigerate overnight.
Season with garlic and/or onion powder. Wrap in foil.
Bake 5 hours in a 300° oven.
Refrigerate and slice when cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer until hot. Bake brisket in sauce for 30 minutes in a 350° oven (or you can serve along side).
I had to learn how to make barbecue when we came to Texas and this is by far the best I've found.
Belly-up now, ya' hear!

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Mix broccoli, potatoes, rice, onion, butter and water in a soup pot. Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Heat, but do not boil.

title: carnation five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat. Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edge of pan.)
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until well blended.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Boil for 30 seconds before adding the chocolate chips.
Let cool slightly and spread.
Great on brownies.

title: waldorf coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding enough mayonnaise to moisten. Toss lightly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin.
Stir in one cup cheese until heated.
Place mixture into flour tortillas, roll and fold ends.
Place into baking dish, top with remaining cheese and salsa.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: bean and hamburger hot dish
directions: Fry beef, bacon and onion; drain grease.
Add celery salt, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, molasses and egg and beat well. Sift flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill.
Form 1-inch balls.
Dip in water, then roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot spinach spread
directions: Mix together over stove.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, cook chicken with salt and pepper, covered with water, until tender.
Take chicken out of pot and put in large mixing bowl.
Chop all vegetables in small pieces.
Add to pot in which chicken was cooked.
Cook slowly until tender.
Remove bones from chicken.
Chop chicken in small pieces.
Add soup to cover vegetables.
Simmer until well heated.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice and boil potatoes.
Drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Saute onions.
Fry or microwave bacon to crispy and crumble or use bacon bits.
Combine potatoes, liquid, onions, bacon, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat and stir.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Do not boil.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Lay the chicken in large piece of foil and put in an 11 x 13-inch glass pan.
Dice the celery and onion and put around chicken.
Pour wine over all of it.
Close foil up tightly and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Use a flat 4-quart Pyrex baking dish.
Butter bottom and sides of baking dish; sprinkle with sugar.
Mix together and pour into prepared baking dish.
Add the green pepper last of all.
Bake for 1 hour in center of 350° oven.

title: country breakfast
directions: Toast English muffins.
Fry sausage and crumble.
Layer sausage, cheese, gravy and eggs on muffin.
Put in hot oven until cheese melts.

title: cheese nachos
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger together; drain.
Mix meat and cheese and soups together in a crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve over nachos.

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Dip chicken breast in butter. Roll in mixture of cheese, crackers and garlic salt. Place in baking dish. Pour unused butter over top of chicken. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° until chicken is tender and well done.

title: peach pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple and peaches on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour dry cake mix on top; cut up butter and spread or place on top. Add juices on top of cake mix evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: invalid's tea
directions: Bring the milk quickly to the scalding point and pour it over the tea.
Let the two infuse four minutes.
Strain and serve with or without sugar.
Tea made by this method nourishes as well as stimulates.

title: easy chocolate crackles
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water and shortening.
Mix with a spoon until well blended.
Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: rissotto alla milanese
directions: In small saucepan, heat chicken broth with saffron just until hot.
Set aside.

title: fish stew
directions: Clean fish and cut into pieces; wash in salted water.
Coat fish with flour and fry until lightly brown.
Put oil in saucepan. Add the flour and stir until light brown.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Place the tomatoes, pepper and salt.
Let it cook for 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and fried fish.
Simmer over medium heat until thickened and well cooked.
Serve with boiled rice, yams or potatoes.

title: mother's raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins and water for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add egg, sugar, flour and salt to raisins, stirring all while it cooks.
Cook until it thickens and flavor with vanilla.
Pour into a pie crust and top with crust.
Bake at 350° until desired brownness.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes and place on a paper towel in oven in a circle about 1-inch apart.
Cook on High (maximum power) 12 to 16 minutes.
Potatoes may feel firm when done; let stand to soften. Do not overcook, as potatoes will dehydrate.
Remove 1/4-inch horizontal slice from top of each potato.
Using teaspoon, remove centers to a mixing bowl.
(Leave shells intact.)
Add sour cream, salt and pepper to potato pulp and beat vigorously until smooth. Divide mixture evenly in shells, mounding if necessary.
Place potatoes in circle on microproof plate.
Cook on High (maximum power) for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 4 servings. Total cooking time:
16 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Mix can of soup with chicken stock in saucepan over heat until it reaches a boil.	Add cut up chicken pieces.
Pour into a baking dish.
Melt margarine; add flour and buttermilk; mix well.	Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer this twice (beginning with broccoli) in a 9 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Dot each layer of the cracker crumbs with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cherry bars
directions: Mix flour, margarine and powdered
sugar.
Press
in
x
9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake
until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes; cool.
Cut into bars 1 x 2-inches.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put into a bag with white sugar and cinnamon; shake well.
Layer biscuits, nuts and cream cheese (if desired), in alternating layers, in a nonstick Bundt pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy kettle, bring sugar and milk to a boil after mixing well.
Let boil to soft ball stage (about 5 minutes).
Do not stir.
Remove from heat; add marshmallow and creamy peanut butter.
Can add vanilla (optional).
Mix well and pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: morgan goo-losh
directions: Cook macaroni in water.
Fry hamburger, onion and green pepper until done.
Add all other ingredients except macaroni and let simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Then add macaroni and cook about 15 minutes longer.
Good with crackers or cornbread and green salad.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Add brown sugar and pecans; stir well.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon pineapple juice; set juice aside.
Arrange pineapple slices in a single layer over brown sugar mixture; set skillet aside.
Place cherries in center of each pineapple slice.
Beat egg yolks at medium speed of an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add dry mixture to yolk mixture.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold egg whites into batter.
Spoon batter evenly over pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small balls.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Double recipe and form into one large ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and serve with crackers.

title: cinnamon pull apart
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
In a bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in mix, layer one row at a time in pan. Then sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Repeat until all biscuits are done.
Use 1/2 cup butter or oleo to cover biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Lightly grease 10 inch pie plate. Fry bacon and crumble. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour in pie plate. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Place half of strawberries in a bowl.
Sprinkle with half of sugar.
Repeat layers.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes, then combine potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and onion powder.
Whip and mash until fluffy.
Add small amount of milk, if needed.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate or freeze until needed.
When ready to bake, drizzle melted margarine over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: phyllo-crust chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken breast halves into 1-inch chunks.
Peel and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Dice onion.
In a 12-inch, high rim frying pan, over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook chicken, stirring frequently until tender and it loses its pink color. Remove with slotted spoon to plate.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies
directions: Start heating oven to 400°.
Sift the flour with baking soda. Mix
shortening,
brown
sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and
egg
until
well
blended.
Stir in half of flour mixture, then nuts, apple and raisins.
Blend in apple juice, then remaining flour mixture.
Onto greased cookie sheet, drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart.
Bake 11 to 14 minutes
or until
done.
While cookies are still hot, spread thinly with Vanilla Glaze.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: red onion salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bacon and onion cornbread
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, about 5 minutes; set aside. Cook bacon until crispy; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine cornbread, bacon in bits, salt, baking soda and pepper.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Gradually add buttermilk mixture and onions to cornbread mixture stirring constantly.
Pour into a greased 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch oblong pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Rinse chickens with water and dry.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and enough flour to stick lightly.
In large skillet or electric frying pan, brown half the chicken at a time in hot oil.
Remove from skillet.
Add onions and curry to oil left in skillet and cook only until tender, not brown.
Add chopped apples, tomato juice plus water, raisins, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sugar and soup.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cook, covered, on low heat for about 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Serve sauce left in pan over chicken and rice.
