Serves 8. May be served with condiments such as chopped peanuts, coconut, crumbled cooked bacon, sieved hard-cooked egg, finely chopped onion or chives.

title: hash and potatoes on shingles
directions: Dice potatoes (enough to feed everybody you are serving). Boil potatoes until done.
In a frying pan, combine grease, flour and water.
This makes a pan of light brown gravy.
Mix corned beef hash with gravy.
Add onions.
Add steak sauce, enough to give flavor.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Drain potatoes.
Pour gravy mix with corned beef hash over potatoes.
Add water, if needed, to cover potatoes.
Let simmer together a few minutes. Serve over bread.
Two pieces of bread smothered with hash and potatoes is one serving.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Chill a large can of Pet milk (make sure it shakes thick, but not frozen).
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, use 1 package graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine (melted).
Mix together well.
Use the back of the spoon and press in corners and up on the sides of the pan.
It falls down sometimes, but keep going, it will stay up. Place in refrigerator to set.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift all dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and flavoring, beating constantly.
Fold in nuts and apples; blend well.
Bake in large sheet pan greased and floured well in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until done in center.

title: light dinner rolls
directions: Heat milk, water and 1/4 cup butter in saucepan until very warm (120° to 130°).
Stir together 3 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add warm liquid mixture to dry ingredients and beat with electric mixer on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board or pastry cloth.
Cover dough with bowl and let rest for 10 minutes.
Knead just until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Place dough in a large greased bowl, turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm draft-free area until doubled in bulk, about 45 minutes.
Punch dough down.
Shape into rolls, as desired.
Place on pans.
Cover and let rise in warm draft-free area until doubled in bulk, about 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans; place on wire racks.
Brush with melted butter.
Serve hot.
Makes about 24 rolls.

title: finland casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook turnips, covered, in a small amount of boiling salted water for 4 minutes; add zucchini and onion. Continue cooking 3 minutes more; drain.
In a large mixing bowl combine turnips, zucchini, onion, tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower, 6 tablespoons of the butter or margarine, wine, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss the crackers with the remaining butter; sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: j.o.'s swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and season with salt and pepper. Coat each piece with flour and brown in a small amount of oil. Remove each piece once browned.
Once all are browned, add steak sauce to the crumbs left in oil and mix well.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper and wilt every so slightly.
Add the can of tomatoes and stir well.
Place steak back in pot (may have to stack on top of each other) and try to push some pieces down into gravy. Cover and cook in a 300° oven for 2 hours.
Remove from oven and take meat out of gravy.
Add water if more gravy is needed.
To thicken, add 1 tablespoon of cornstarch to water before adding to mixture.
Heat on high on stove top and serve over rice.
Yum! Yum!

title: coffee cake muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, nuts, flour, cinnamon and melted butter. Set aside.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl and cut in shortening. Combine egg and milk and add to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened.
In greased muffin tins, spoon small amount of batter. Add a layer of nut mixture. Add more batter and top with nut mixture.
Repeat until 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: catfish amandine
directions: Rub the catfish well with salt and cayenne pepper.
Set aside. Lightly beat egg whites until foamy.
Blend together the beaten egg whites with the cornstarch.

title: deviled wheeler eggs
directions: Boil eggs, peel and cool.
Cut eggs in half to be filled. Serve yolks to add to mixture for filling.
Mix balance of ingredients for filling.
Stuff eggs.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve on a platter.
Great for parties!

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower using package directions. Drain.
Saute onion in butter in saucepan. Add rice, broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms, cheese soup and milk.
Mix well.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: stromboli(light and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown turkey, onion, green pepper and garlic over medium-high heat.
Drain fat; add spaghetti sauce and cool.

title: fluffy lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Cool until thick.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, pecans and whipped cream.
Chill until firm.
Serve squares on lettuce leaves.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix with margarine; set aside.
Place zucchini and onion in pot with enough water to cover.
Boil 5 minutes; drain and cool.
Mix zucchini and onion with soup, carrots and sour cream.
Place half of stuffing in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour zucchini mixture in and cover with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cover with foil until last 10 minutes.

title: sausage twirls
directions: Divide crescent roll dough into 4 rectangles.
Divide 1 pound of uncooked sausage into 4 parts.
Spread sausage evenly onto the 4 dough rectangles. Roll up each rectangle (like a jelly roll) and slice.
Gently flatten slices with hand and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done.
Excellent for breakfast, a snack or hors d'oeuvres.

title: deer jerky
directions: Trim off fat; cut meat with the grain 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick in strips as long as possible.
Partially frozen meat is easier to cut.
Combine all other ingredients in bowl; stir until dissolved. Pour over meat strips; cover tightly and marinate overnight. Remove from sauce.
Arrange strips close together, but do not overlap, on rack.
We hang them on the rack by paper clips.
Make sure to put tinfoil in bottom of oven.
Bake in a 150° oven for 7 hours.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Add slightly beaten egg, cream and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Dough may be chilled if desired. (I always do.)
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake in 325° oven 5 to 8 minutes until delicately browned.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage; drain.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Mix with Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano. Spread on party rye.
Put on cookie sheet.
Stick in freezer. (Once frozen, put into bags.)
When you remove from freezer, bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: mozzarella marinara
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil. Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, water, sugar, salt and bay leaf. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 - 30 minutes or until thickened. Serve with mozzarella cheese sticks or cheese bread sticks.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Grind or chop vegetables (I use food processor).
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight or 6 to 8 hours.
Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Drain well, then combine sugar, water, vinegar and spices.
Pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling and boil for 3 minutes.
Seal in jars.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes after water begins to boil.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and small amount of milk together until all is dissolved.
Add corn syrup and balance of milk.
Boil slowly for 12 minutes.
Stir to prevent burning.
Makes 1 pint.

title: brenda's pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1 crust.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie pan and top with second crust.
Seal and crimp edges.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brown rice(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a deep 3-quart casserole.
Heat covered on simmer for 25 minutes or tender.
Let stand covered 10 minutes.
Pour rice into colander and rinse with hot water.

title: sweet and sour beef fajitas
directions: Cut beef into thin strips. Heat oil in skillet over high heat. Add beef. Stir fry 2-3 minutes, until brown. Drain. Stir in salsa, ketchup, brown sugar and mustard. Cook 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly until hot. Spoon into tortillas. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, and sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Steam chicken until tender.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix with remainder of ingredients except crumbs.
Turn chicken mixture into greased two-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs or chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered in moderate oven (350°) until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: god love 'em cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: sharon's macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed. While macaroni cooks, in separate bowl, mix beaten egg, 2 to 3 cups milk and seasonings. (You add more or less milk, depending on how dry or wet you like macaroni.)

title: mint tea *
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour over tea bags and mint.
Cover and leave for 5 minutes.
Strain tea.
Add lemon juice.

title: layered tostada bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, beans, chili and olives.
Mix baking mix, corn meal, milk, egg and oil until moistened; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Spread in dish.
Spoon beef mixture over dough.
Mix the remaining ingredients; spoon over beef mixture.
Bake 30 minutes; let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Heat saucepan and add 1/2 butter; cut chicken in halves and flour with salt, pepper and garlic (mashed).
Saute in butter until light brown on both sides; remove to plate.
Add remaining butter and saute mushrooms 2 to 3 minutes.
Add wine and reduce by one half.
Add bouillon; reduce slightly.
Add chicken; cook until sauce thickens.
Add parsley.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set about 30 minutes. Serve.

title: curried carrots(4 persons)
directions: Trim carrots and boil in the usual way.
Prepare curry sauce as follows.
Melt fat in saucepan; add onion (chopped) and fry a few minutes.
Add curry powder and flour and fry, stirring from time to time, for a few minutes longer.
Stir in stock or water and when boiling, season to taste.
Simmer gently about 30 minutes.
Add cooked carrots to curry sauce in saucepan and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with a garnish of cooked rice.
(GF)

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put drained spinach in buttered casserole.
Add water chestnuts, sour cream and soup.
Salt and pepper and mix.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no fat green beans
directions: Place beans and ingredients in Dutch oven or large boiler. Cover with water.
Cook 2 hours or until tender.
Remove cover and boil on medium-high to reduce liquid, if desired.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Saute onions, leek and potatoes in butter over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add stock and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Puree potato-leek mixture in blender.
Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper.
Add half and half.
Return to heat and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ginger crisps
directions: Mix hard, roll thin and bake.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Burn 1/2 cup sugar in steel skillet to a deep brown.
Add water and shake well until all sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk with flour that has been sifted 3 times with baking powder and soda.
Stir in burnt sugar liquid.
Then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° until done.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Simmer about 15 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Add rice last.
Cover and steam until rice is done.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine soups and Cheez Whiz.
Add celery, onion, rice and broccoli.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: praline meltaways
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray bottoms and sides of 12 regular-size muffin cups with cooking spray.
Stir together butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Divide mixture evenly over muffin cups.
Stir baking mix, milk and granulated sugar until soft dough forms.
Place a spoonful of dough in each muffin cup.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes until golden brown.
Turn pan upside down onto cookie sheet.
Leave pan over biscuits a few minutes to allow brown sugar mixture to drizzle over biscuits.
Replace topping from pan onto biscuits.
Cool slightly before serving; serve warm.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, eggs, coconut, sugar, margarine, milk, baking powder and pecans.
Pour into 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon pineapple over warm cake.
Let cool.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Beat together with mixer until smooth.
Add 1 pound miniature marshmallows and 1 can crushed and drained pineapple.
Beat 1 pint whipping cream until stiff and fold into the mixture.
Put in glass cake pan and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: peach glace pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Bring preserves to a boil; stir in softened gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add almond extract.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Arrange peach halves in crust with cut sides down.
Pour gelatin mixture over peaches.
Cool in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: waikiki meat balls
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, salt, egg, ginger and milk. Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonful into balls.
Melt shortening in a large skillet. Brown and cook meat balls.
Remove meat balls and keep warm.

title: tangy seafood sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: memow's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add 1 cup of chopped pecans. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: coffee kuchen
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and brown sugar.
Cut in shortening and butter or margarine.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for topping.
Combine coffee, milk and soda.
Add to remaining flour mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs. Spoon into prepared muffin pans, filling half full.
Add cinnamon to topping mixture; sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix and let set awhile or overnight.

title: meat pie
directions: Saute onion in oil with beef and pork; drain off grease.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put bottom pie crust in pie pan.
Fill with meat mixture.
Put top crust on.
Make slits in top crust. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: ono pizza fritta(fried dough)
directions: Dissolve
1/2 square of yeast or package
of
yeast,
1 teaspoon sugar and 1 cup warm water; let set to rise.
Measure in a large bowl 8 cups flour and 1 tablespoon	salt.
Mix
in yeast mixture and Crisco, adding about 3 to 3 1/2 cups of warm water; mix well.
Add a little oil on hands while mixing.	Let rise double.
Punch
down;
let rise again.
Pinch
off
and shape into desired shape.
Fry in oil
until
brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Saute onion and pepper in butter. Cook vermicelli in broth; drain (save some).
Combine all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May need to add broth if it seems dry. Freezes well.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put into freezer container of ice cream maker.
Add milk to the freeze line.
Freeze per your ice cream maker's instructions.

title: walnut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; mix well and set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients then add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in loaf pans.

title: dirt salad
directions: Put melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush all but 6 cookies, put in pan and spread and pat firmly.
Mix milk, pudding mix and food coloring for 3 to 4 minutes until thickened.
Add ice cream. Stir until smooth., Pour over cookies.
Spread whipped topping on ice cream mixture.
Crush remaining cookies and sprinkle on top. Refrigerate.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; place, skin side up, in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place under broiler; brown on both sides, turning skin side back up.
Mix all other ingredients together; spoon over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, in blender or with electric mixer on low speed for 3 minutes.
(Also can be whisked.) Pour into pie pan, let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cake top pie
directions: Combine the sugar, flour and pinch of salt.
Beat together lemon juice, egg yolks and milk.
Add to the first part and beat. Beat egg whites; add to the mixture.
Pour into unbaked crust. Bake for 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: marinated shrimp and cucumber
directions: Combine first three ingredients and set aside.
Cook, peel and devein shrimp.
Mix shrimp, cucumbers and onion with olive oil mixture.
Bring to boil the next seven ingredients and simmer 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour the herb mixture over the shrimp and stir. Pour capers, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice over mixture. Chill 8 hours, stirring once or twice.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits thin and cut in half.
Peel 5 apples and quarter them.
Wrap each quarter with 1/2 biscuit.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and water.
Heat and pour over apples.
Melt margarine and pour over this.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Baste often with sauce that cooks out of apples.

title: turkey breast marsala
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Saute turkey slices in single layer, 1 minute on each side, until golden.
Add more butter as needed.
Remove turkey slices as browned and keep warm.
Return all slices to skillet overlapping; sprinkle with pepper.
Place a slice of Prosciutto and cheese on each slice of turkey.
Pour Marsala over all.
Cook, covered, 3 to 5 minutes, until heated through and cheese is all melted.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and watercress, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in 4 1/2 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Drain beans. Add 4 quarts water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender.
Stir sauteed vegetables and next 6 ingredients into beans; cook, uncovered, 1 hour, stirring occasionally and adding additional water if necessary.
Bake sausage at 350° for 20 minutes; drain well.
Stir sausage into bean mixture.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaves.
Stir in chopped parsley.
Serve over Oven Rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cajun duck
directions: Boil ducks with no seasoning.
Save broth; strip meat off bones and put aside.
Cook rice in broth, adding water as needed. Cook separately bell pepper, onion and celery; simmer until tender.
In large pan, cook tomatoes, Ro-Tel and picante sauce. Add cinnamon, sage, marjoram and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all cooked ingredients.
Simmer on stove for 2 hours, uncovered. Serves approximately 15.

title: pink party salad
directions: Place first three ingredients in a saucepan and heat until marshmallows melt.
Refrigerate until the mixture starts to gel. Remove from refrigerator and fold in the last three ingredients and chill.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions, pepper and garlic.
Mix in soup and chili.
Pour in casserole.
Top with cheese and Fritos.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 12 hours before serving.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain fat.
Combine Ro-Tel and soup.
In microwave-safe pan, layer tortilla chips, soup mix, hamburger and cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave for 12 minutes.
Top with cheese and microwave another 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sausage
directions: Boil a salted hogs head, cut up , until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Remove bones.
Grind or cut up remaining meat until fine.
Press into a flat container until "set."
Slice and pour diluted vinegar over.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground chuck or beef in skillet with chopped onion. After browned, drain liquid off and discard.
Cook rice.
Boil peppers until almost soft in boiling water.
Mix ground chuck and rice together; add tomatoes or sauce.
Mix together.
Stuff peppers and bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix
with
electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 3 large layers, ice.

title: carrot and corn nibbles
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar and dry mustard.
Stir in 1/3 cup water and remaining ingredients, except corn.
Bring to a boil, then let cool 20 minutes.
Place corn in bowl.
Add carrots and marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook
onions slowly with
butter
and
oil
in
covered saucepan for 15 minutes.
Uncover
and
raise heat to moderate and stir in salt and sugar.
Cook
to 40 minutes, stirring constantly, until the onions
have turned a deep golden brown. Sprinkle in flour and
stir
for
3 minutes.
Combine bouillon and boiling water and add to
mixture.
Add wine and season to taste. Simmer, partially covered,
for
to
minutes, skimming occasionally.
You may
also top with Swiss cheese to serve.

title: diet soup
directions: Cut all vegetables in medium pieces and cover with water. Boil for 10 minutes. Add onion soup mix. Turn on low heat and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: potato mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Peel potatoes; cook with garlic in boiling salted water.
Meanwhile, saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Drain potatoes; discard garlic.
Whip potatoes with 1/4 cup butter, cream, egg yolks, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in mushrooms and parsley.
Spoon into casserole.
Melt rest of butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine celery, onion, mayonnaise, vinegar and lemon juice. Add and mix well to the shrimp.
Enjoy!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion and drain.
Add dry seasonings. Stir in tomato sauce, corn and kidney beans.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes on low-medium heat.
Cover the casserole with bite size corn chips.
Top with shredded cheese.
Allow cheese to melt and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain and mash with potato masher.
Add cracker crumbs, milk, egg, salt and pepper. Put buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Add margarine and cheese to carrots.
Let cool.
Add eggs and milk.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients lightly and bake in an 8 or 9-inch baking
dish
or
iron skillet in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
(Grease and heat skillet before filling.)

title: tomato bacon cups
directions: Chop bacon, ham, tomato, onion, and cheese.
Add mayonnaise and basil.
Cut biscuits into quarters, place each quarter into a mini muffin pan.
Use a wood spoon dusted with flour to mash into the cup.
Add above mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: light zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar; beat well.
Add flavoring and zucchini; beat.
Mix dry ingredients together; stir in and add nuts; mix well.
Bake in small loaf pans or in oiled cans (size 2 1/2 pounds) at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in cans until bread will remove easily, then cool on wire rack.
This freezes well and is an ideal way to use up those monsters.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into gallon freezer. Freeze according to manufacturers instructions. Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: my favorite french fried potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes into thin shoestring size.
Fry in hot grease until golden brown or deep brown.
Stir occasionally.
Do not crowd potatoes in pan.
Drain on absorbent paper placed on a paper plate.
Good eating!!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and peppers. Mix cornbread mix as directed and add cream style corn. Layer 1/2 of the cornbread mix in 9X13 casserole dish, then add meat mixture, drained beans and cheese. Top entire dish with rest of cornbread mixture. Bake at 350° until cornbread is golden brown.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in pan at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook in a large pan (roaster) in medium oven (350°) until no water runs off when put in dish.
Put in jars and seal.
This makes 10 to 14 pints of apple butter.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat the yolks and corn lightly and set aside.
Combine the flour, sugar, salt, butter and pepper.
Add milk slowly, beating until smooth.
Combine the 2 mixtures and pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake in a pan of water at 350° for 1 hour or until custard is firm.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni for 8 minutes and drain it.
Mix canned milk, whole milk and beaten eggs.
Mix macaroni, milk mixture, melted margarine and 2 cups of grated cheese.
Pour into crock-pot.
Top with 1 cup of grated cheese.
Do not stir.
Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill or freeze ahead of time.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 teaspoon milk and sugar.
Stir with wire whisk.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour milk in bowl, add pudding and stir with whisk for 1 minute.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix the pudding, Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Fold in the pineapple, oranges and nuts.
Let stand 24 hours.
Serves 14.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Clean and peel the potatoes.
Grate very finely.
Add the onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
If the mixture becomes too runny, add a tablespoon of flour.
Fry small pancakes in a hot pan with a little oil.
Turn the pancakes to brown on both sides.
Very good along or with a meat sauce.
Often served with applesauce or sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Clean fresh fruit.
Drain any canned fruit that's being used. Combine the two to equal 6 cups.
Reserve 2 cups for top.
Combine buttermilk and pudding mix in large bowl.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour over the 4 cups of fruit.
Top with reserved 2 cups of fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare mix as directed on package.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. In pan over low heat, melt caramels, milk, butter and chips. Stir until smooth.
Remove cake from oven and pour melted ingredients over cake.
Top with nuts and pour remaining batter over this.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pat into 9x13 pan.
Melt chocolate chips and frost over top in pan. When chocolate in set, cut into small squares. These taste much like Reese's cups.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and water with 2 cups berries. Heat and boil at medium heat for about 1 minute.
Pour over 2 cups berries in baked pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: jessica's rice pilaf
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook rice and onion in butter until rice is golden, stirring often.
Add chicken broth, water and salt. Bring up to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes.
Fluff up with a fork.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: darned if i know cake
directions: In ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, mix pineapple with pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix on top. Sprinkle coconut over cake and nuts over coconut. Thinly slice margarine and place over all.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat and onion (drain).
Add other ingredients; cook for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice or with crackers.

title: cranberry freeze drink
directions: Mix and freeze.
Just before serving, fill glass with 3/4 slush and 1/4 7-Up.
Delicious at holiday time.
Keeps in freezer for several months.

title: garden chicken and stuffing
directions: Spread 3 cups dried stuffing on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
In large bowl, stir together chicken, broccoli, mushroom soup, chicken soup and pimiento.
Spoon over stuffing; sprinkle with cheese.
In medium bowl, combine all remaining ingredients, except 3 cups dried stuffing and butter. Pour over chicken mixture.
Cover; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle with 3 cups remaining dried stuffing; drizzle with butter.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until set and heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: blind date cake
directions: Combine dates, 1 teaspoon soda and hot water. Let stand until cool. Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time; beat well. Sift together flour, teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon soda. Beat in cooled date mixture. Turn into a well-greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together chocolate chips, remaining sugar and nuts. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: dockside summer salad
directions: In mixing bowl, whisk together minced shallot, apple cider vinegar, Dijon mustard and chopped tarragon.
Gradually whisk in extra virgin olive oil until thickened.
In large bowl, toss apple cider vinegar-tarragon mixture with mixed salad greens.
Transfer salad to serving bowl and sprinkle cranberries and walnuts on top. Makes 2 servings.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy 3 to 4 minutes.
Beat in flour, baking soda, powder and cocoa until well blended.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix thoroughly in a saucepan the sugar, cornstarch, salt, shredded coconut and egg yolks.
Stir in gradually until smooth a mixture of evaporated milk and water.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cover and cool thoroughly.
Put in 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Spread with meringue.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup coconut. Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely before cutting with wet knife.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Mix together.
While sauce is cooking, bake meat balls for 1 hour.
Put meat balls into sauce and cook 2 more hours.
Cook Mostaccioli noodles and drain.
Pour sauce and meat balls over noodles.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, pepper, onion, peas, cheese and meat in oblong dish.
Spread Miracle Whip over like frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: brown rice
directions: Cook onion, rice and margarine in heavy skillet until brown. Mix consomme and mushroom soup and add to the rice mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Save broth from chicken when cooking.
Crush Doritos.
Heat soup and tomatoes together.
Layer chicken, onion (if desired), cheese, Doritos and soup in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1 1/2 cups broth over; bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked apple pudding cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pork tenderloin a la asparagus
directions: Pound pork to flatten.
Brown in margarine.
Set aside.
In same skillet, blend together soup and milk; add other ingredients. Return meat to skillet.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until tender.
Serve sauce on top meat.
In place of skillet cooking, may bake in 350° oven about 2 hours.
Makes four servings.

title: salsa dip
directions: Using a shallow dish, layer in order given.
Serve with chips.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch or flour and melted butter. Use 6 egg yolks.
Stir in with the other ingredients.
Mix well. Add buttermilk, one at a time.
Stir well.
Add vanilla extract. Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Cook in oven until brown. Use your 6 egg whites for meringue.
Beat until fluffy.
Place on pie and brown.
Put enough sugar in meringue to make fluffy and stiff along with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.

title: french vanilla torte
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix the pudding with the cold milk.
Beat the cream cheese and powdered sugar 2 minutes.
Add softened Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust.
Spread pudding mix.
Top with remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and soda with water to first mixture and mix.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nutmeats (if desired). Drop in rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: turkey and green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix contents of vegetable-seasoning packet, water and margarine in large bowl until margarine is melted.
Stir in stuffing crumbs just to moisten; set aside.
Layer turkey and green beans in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk in another bowl until smooth.
Pour over turkey mixture. Spoon stuffing evenly over top.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mike's meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper, eggs, 1/2 can beer, onion and crackers.
Make into small balls, cooking until done.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon in 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towels.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Pour off drippings; reserve 1/4 cup.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup drippings until tender; do not brown.
Add potatoes, chicken broth and salt; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add turkey, undrained corn, cream-style corn, light cream and pepper; heat well.
To serve, garnish each bowl with bacon bits and parsley.
Makes 3 quarts or 9 servings.

title: minute fudge icing
directions: Mix above and bring to boil. Boil 1 minute. Cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla. Beat till thick enough to spread.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour dressing over cut up vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma's lye soap
directions: Cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into a wooden container lined with cloth; cool. When hard, cut in squares.

title: corn beef casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onions, salt and pepper (do not brown).
Boil egg noodles and drain.
Drain grease from hamburger and mix all ingredients, including sour cream.
Melt margarine in a skillet. Tear bread into small pieces and add to margarine.
Mix well. Place meat mixture into casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake in 450° oven until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rich roll dough for butterhorns or rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add hot water (125°).
Mix well. Add slightly beaten eggs and remaining flour. Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead.
In you have bread hook for mixer, do it in there for 3 1/2 minutes and then turn over and do for 1 minute.
If not, knead for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let raise in warm place until double in bulk.
Divide into 3 parts.

title: salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain pineapple and add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin, then add cream cheese that has been slightly softened.
Chill until slightly thick, then beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Put in gelatin ring and chill.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil together; let cool.
Squeeze out cabbage; mix in 2 red and 2 green peppers (chopped) and 1 stalk celery.
Pour cooled syrup over and put in containers and freeze.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs, butter, sugar and molasses until very thick and smooth.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients together.
Add flour and water alternately to the egg mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Place batter in a well buttered and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes in 400° oven.
Let gingerbread cool 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Set half of stuffing mix aside.
Mix other ingredients.
Top with the remaining stuffing mix and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled.
Serves 6 people.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Shake before using.

title: girdle buster
directions: First Layer:
Blend butter and flour.
Add nuts, then press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°, until light brown, then cool.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Cook rotini and drain.
Cook beef, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and onion for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring until brown.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and rotini.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish, top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetable stir-fry over rice
directions: Chicken and Vegetables:
Prepare vegetables and meat.
Chop vegetables in bite-size pieces.
Slice chicken breast in bite-size pieces or purchase chicken stir-fry.

title: rice and beef
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in oil.
Add ginger, pepper strips, bouillon, soy sauce and sherry.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: herb loaf
directions: Soften butter and cream with parsley, oregano, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Cut loaf of bread in slices.
Spread both sides with the herb butter.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Five minutes before serving, open the foil and let the top of loaf get crusty again.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves six.

title: lentil soup
directions: Mix all of the above in large pot.
Bring to a boil then simmer for 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: apricot fluff
directions: Drain apricots and add enough water to make 2 cups. Heat and use to dissolve jello.
Then add 2 cups cold water. Let jello set only until slightly thickened.
Mix up with wire whip and fold in apricots and Cool Whip. Put into pretty glass bowl and chill well. So pretty and so good!

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to
Combine
all
ingredients in large bowl and mix at	low
speed
of	electric mixer until blended. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto baking sheet and bake for 7 to 9 minutes. Cool 2 minutes.
Cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Stir in next three ingredients.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.

title: mary ellen's best sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until well browned.
Add peppers.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add to pan with pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar, ginger and garlic powder.
Bring to a full boil. Prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve chicken over rice. Makes 4 servings, 350 calories per serving with 7 grams of fat.

title: creamy horseradish and "dill meat balls"
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, water, horseradish, dill and salt in bowl.
Shape meat into sixteen 2-inch balls.
Put balls 1/2 inch apart on broiler pan.
In a 5-quart pan, Add remaining oil and whisk in flour, cook stirring 2 minutes.
Whisk in broth, remaining dill, salt and pepper until thickened, 2 minutes.
Add meat balls to sauce.
Simmer, covered, basting occasionally for 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and remaining horseradish. Serve over noodles.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef; drain, if necessary.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: swartzes potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving half of cheese for top.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Reduce temperature to 325° if using glass dish.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut bacon into bite sized pieces.
In large pot or Dutch oven, saute bacon and onion with butter until tender.
Add cabbage and fry till done, stirring occasionally.
You may need to add more butter depending on the flavor desired.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 2 round 8-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until dough is no longer sticky.
Grease a large bowl; turn dough to coat all sides and top.
Cover with towel and let set 8 to 12 hours.
Do not refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chess pie
directions: Line cupcake pans with pie pastry.
Fill with mixture and bake in moderate oven.
My mother made my favorite treat (chess pies) many times for me.
I can remember the wonderful aroma coming from the kitchen when I got home from school.
Sometimes I hid mine so I could guarantee my share.
When I grew up and became a teacher the treat was just as special when I got home, except that I hid mine from my husband and children, instead of just my brother.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch squares.
Brown in hot oil.
Remove from pan.
Add gravy mix and water; bring to boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients except noodles.
Return meat to pan; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring as needed.
Add bay leaf.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine 2/3 cup sugar, flour and salt in 2-quart saucepan; stir in milk gradually.
Cook on high until mixture starts to steam; switch to third and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Switch to low.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks; slowly stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool and chill in refrigerator.
Add 2/3 cup coconut and vanilla extract.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and salt, then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Stir in marshmallows until almost blended. Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan. Cool. Cut.

title: jello salad 1
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add pineapple and blueberries.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with whipped cream or topping.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot stuffing casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, cheese and carrots.
Spoon into a 2-quart greased casserole dish. Toss bread stuffing mix with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spoon on top of carrot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ladye's wedding mocha punch
directions: Mix together first 4 (or 5) ingredients.
Put in refrigerator. Gradually add 2 gallons of milk to mixture.
Garnish with whipped ice cream.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, chocolate shavings, cherries and chocolate syrup on top.

title: orange peach pie(for diabetics)
directions: In a saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt and water until smooth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in sweetener and gelatin. Cool. Fold in peaches. Pour into crust and refrigerate for 2 hours or until serving. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Scrub and boil whole yams or sweet potatoes for 30 minutes. Drain and cool 30 minutes.
Cut yams in half lengthwise and scoop out meat.
In a large mixing bowl, whip yams with butter or margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar, and cream or half and half.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with walnuts and remaining brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or on High in microwave for 20 minutes.

title: stewed rice
directions: Cook rice, sugar and milk on low heat until rice is thoroughly done.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Add cinnamon and butter on top when finished.

title: bacon and cheddar potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes in water till soft. Drain. Place in a mixing bowl. Add butter and cheese while potatoes are still hot. Add a little milk and start the mixer on low speed. Increase the speed and add milk as needed until the potatoes are light and fluffy. Add the bacon and blend in well. Check seasonings. Serve warm.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Shake chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in shallow 2-quart baking dish in 400° oven.
Put chicken skin side down in dish and bake 20 minutes.
Remove chicken and put 2 to 3 cups boiling water in dish with remaining ingredients.
Mix well and arrange chicken skin side up on top.
Bake in oven 40 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Egg noodles or any pasta may be substituted if you don't like rice.

title: lemon bars #1
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in food processor.
Pat into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat the next 4 ingredients in food processor and pour over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Scrumptious!

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 325° until rice is tender (approximately 30 minutes).
(Sausage may be cooked some and crumbled and drained to cut down on grease.)

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix 1/2
of
Cool
Whip
with
cream cheese.
Pour into bottom of crusts.	Then put on a layer of berries and top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: cyn's potatoes delish
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and place in 3-quart greased casserole.
Cover with crumb mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Serves 24.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar thoroughly with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake
in
glass
Pyrex
dish
at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test by inserting knife in edge of custard to see if done.
You can vary flavor by adding fruits of your choice.

title: island chicken appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cover skewers with water; let soak 5 minutes.
Mix preserves, dressing and soup mix in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Thread chicken strips into individual skewers.
Place in 15 x 10-inch foil-lined pan.
Pour dressing mixture over chicken, thoroughly coating chicken.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: spicy bacon bean pot
directions: Prepare onions to fry.
Have hot fat in frying pan.
When onions are seasoned and frying nicely, slide into oven.
Place over the fire another frying pan.
When fat is smoking hot in same, put a nice one inch thick steak into same, sear on both sides quickly in hot fat.

When done place on platter, season, remove onions from the oven, drain all the fat off the onions. Cover steak with onions and serve at once with a few slices of lemon and tomatoes and a small sprig of parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken breast pieces in large (11 x 13-inch) baking pan. Layer slices of Swiss cheese over chicken.
Stir white wine or water into soup; pour over cheese.
Melt butter and mix into stuffing.
(Ignore the stuffing package instructions.)
Layer stuffing mixture over the soup.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
With wooden spoon beat until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Combine 1/4 cup butter or margarine, melted and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from pan.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: caramel-apple streusel
directions: Arrange the apples in a microwave dish.
Stir together caramel topping, water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples.
In a small bowl combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter, until the mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cook for about 10 to 14 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender; cut in halves and scoop out insides.
Set aside skins; mash insides and add sour cream, chives, butter and enough milk to make stiff consistency.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pile mashed potato mixture back into skins; place in baking dish and return to oven.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place cheese on top; sprinkle with paprika and heat until cheese melts, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: green mansions slaw
directions: Remove center of cabbage, leaving outer leaves to form a shell. Shred cabbage removed from center.
Combine with pineapple, grapes, cucumber and enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Chill; fill cabbage shell.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mincemeat ring cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and beat vigorously 1/2 minute.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 2-quart casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Slice unpeeled apples.
Arrange apple slices in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, combine the flour, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in the margarine with a fork until the mixture is crumbly.
Spread over the fruit.
Bake 40 minutes or until the apples are tender.

title: teriyaki shish kabobs
directions: Combine sugar, ginger, garlic, soy sauce and pineapple juice; heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour marinade over meat in glass or stainless steel bowl.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least overnight.
These are better when allowed to soak for 2 to 3 days.
Alternate pieces of meat with mushrooms, pineapple, onions and peppers on skewers or long bamboo sticks. Barbecue or broil to desired doneness.
Marinade can be heated and thickened with cornstarch and water to use as dipping sauce for meat.

title: hot fried apple pies
directions: Roll out biscuits on a floured board.
Place 2 or 3 tablespoons apple filling on each biscuit.
Fold over and seal edges.
Place in hot pan with just enough grease to cover bottom. Fry until golden brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Measure 6 cups water into pan.
Add cloves and cinnamon and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add tea.
Cover and steep for 10 minutes.
Strain and set aside.

title: dream whip cake recipe
directions: If pudding is in the mix, add 1/4 cup oil.
Beat 4 minutes.

title: elephant ears
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and beaten egg, mixing together.
Stir in flour gradually until smooth.
Mixture does not have to rise.
Break into pieces the size of an egg and roll out in 1/4 inch thick rounds.
Deep fry.
Dust with sugar and cinnamon.
Makes 20 ears.

title: quick quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Put crumbled bacon, cheese and onion on bottom of pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender for 1 minute and pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 apple pie
directions: Cook
apples
well
done.
Sweeten
to
taste.
Spread softened margarine	in a casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix sugar and flour.
Add
milk
and whip until all lumps are out.
Pour over margarine.	Pour apples

and
spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45
minutes
or until done.
Crust will rise to top.	Serve with vanilla ice
cream or Cool Whip.
If you like cinnamon add a little to the cooked apples.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Measure vanilla and soda, but do not mix.
Set aside.
Cook sugar, Karo, and water over low heat until mixture reaches hard ball stage.
Add butter and peanuts.
Cook until golden brown. (Watch carefully.
Burns easily at this point.)
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and soda all at once and stir quickly.
Turn into well buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: red party punch
directions: Dissolve each according to directions.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Place salmon in greased shallow pan.
In saucepan, melt butter and add seasonings; spread over steaks.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon grated onion over each steak.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes, turning once.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put into 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker in order given.
Cover and cook on high for 8 hours.
With wire whisk, stir until meat is shredded.
Serve on hard rolls or burger buns.

title: zarzuela(a shellfish stew)
directions: Saute onion, tomato and garlic in olive oil.
Add turmeric, clams, clam juice and white wine.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, crab and cayenne.
Cover and cook on high until clams open, plus 2 extra minutes.

title: chol-free yeast rolls
directions: Cream together sugar and salt.
Mix yeast with warm water; set aside.
Sift flour; sit it aside.
Add boiling water to sugar and salt mixture; stir until Crisco is melted.
Add cold water, then add yeast mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in flour just until it is well mixed.
Put in bowl that has airtight lid.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Knead a few times when ready to bake. Roll in small balls and place on a cooking sheet sprayed with Pam, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Brush with melted margarine.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add carrots and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except spinach.
Bring to a boil and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add spinach. Heat thoroughly.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add 3/4 teaspoon curry powder.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Use "Can't Fail Crust" but omit the sugar and add 1 teaspoon oregano leaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom patties
directions: Shape meat into thick patties and season to your taste. Cook in
skillet
until
almost done.
Remove patties and save half of the
fat in the skillet.
Add soup mix and stir in fat until well mixed.
Add patties and simmer 5 more minutes.
Mix in sliced mushrooms.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Blend in oil, vanilla and milk.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly, just until moistened.
Fold in berries.
Spoon into well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Serve warm.

title: brandy alexander pie
directions: In a saucepan sprinkle the gelatin over the cold water.
Add 1/3 cup of sugar, salt and egg yolks.
Heat until the gelatin dissolves and the mixture thickens.
Do not boil.
Cool until the mixture mounds; add cognac and creme de cacao.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and gradually add 1/3 cup sugar.
Whip 1 cup of cream and gently fold all three together and turn into crust and chill.

title: tomatoes-mozzarella salad
directions: Layer tomatoes and cheese in shallow dish. In small jar with a tight lid, place oil, vinegar, parsley, onion, basil, salt and pepper. Cover and shake well. Pour over tomatoes and cheese. Cover and refrigerate several hours, occasionally spooning dressing over tomatoes salad.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls about 2-inches round. Place in baking dish.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes covered with wax paper. May be baked in oven at 375° until done.
Top with catsup last few minutes of cooking, if desired.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix hot water with Jell-O.
Add pineapple and cream cheese. May add chopped nuts.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Pickles will last for several weeks.
Makes 12 servings.
May try different spices, garlic, dill, oregano or hot sauce to add a creative flavor.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Scald cabbage.
Combine ground beef, sausage, salt, pepper, garlic salt and meat tenderizer.
Mix with rice.

title: veal and peppers
directions: Brown meat on low flame in very little oil. Do not fully cook meat. Slice green peppers 1/2 to 1 inch wide lengthwise. Add peppers and onion to meat mixture. When peppers get a little soft, throw in remaining ingredients, except the wine. Let simmer for about 1/2 hour; add the wine. If mixture gets a little dry, add water.

title: apple goodie
directions: Place apples in baking dish and cover with 1 cup of sugar. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix butter, oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Spread this mixture over apples and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Add some extra butter to make it juicier.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on package, using 2 round layers.
Mix Cool Whip and 1 1/2 package of frozen coconut, sour cream and 1 cup sugar.
Split the two layers of cake and spread icing between each layer, on sides and top.
Top with remaining coconut.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Sausage should be at a spreadable temperature.
Blend with Tabasco.
Combine biscuit mix and oleo with a fork until crumbly. Mix in water or milk as package directs.
Roll dough into a rectangle; spread sausage evenly and roll-up.
Wrap and store in freezer or refrigerator.
Cut into slices when 1/2 frozen or very cold.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Yield: About 50 cookie size pinwheels.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine the
first 5 ingredients; mix.	Add the remaining ingredients.
Store in covered container in refrigerator. Will keep for
about
6	weeks.	To use, do not mix, just fill greased muffin pans about 2/3 full.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: glaze's hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm milk, then add salt, sugar, oil and eggs. Mix real good.
Lastly, add flour.
If dough is too soft, add more flour.
If too stiff, add a little water.
Let rise to top of bowl; take spoon and work it down.
Put on floured waxed paper.
Get a small amount and shape into rolls.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise again.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken with prosciutto
directions: Slice boneless chicken breast.
Season with salt, pepper and dust with flour.
Panfry in butter and oil, just to light brown (do not overcook).
In large baking dish, place chicken, then a slice of Prosciutto.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Dribble with chicken stock.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° until cheese melts and slightly browns.

title: nancy's mustard glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
In a medium skillet, melt butter.
Stir in mustard and brown sugar.
Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add carrots.
Cook and stir until carrots are glazed and reheat if they have cooled.
Stir in snipped parsley if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: petits pois salad
directions: Drain peas and place in bowl.
Add celery and eggs to peas. Add mayo, then add salt and pepper to taste.

title: "surprise in the middle" cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Fill paper cups 2/3 full of mixture.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Add chocolate chips.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on top of chocolate mixture. Bake according to directions.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Let pan cool before pouring in batter. Add next 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour in pan with margarine, then add peaches on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, green chilies, black olives, Cheddar cheese, green onions and seasoned salt; spread on each shell. Roll up tight. Chill before serving. Slice into 1/2-inch pieces. Serve with salsa.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini; drain.
Cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons oleo.
Stir in soup, sour cream and zucchini.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with 1 cup crushed croutons with oleo, melted.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: doris' excellent fruit torte
directions: Grease and flour a 12 pizza pan, then press the dough into it. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: simple pancake syrup
directions: Cook for 7 minutes stirring constantly.
Add
a tablespoon of maple flavoring.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Sift dry ingredients and spices.
Stir in mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: smoked eye of the round
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl; mix well.
Place roast in a large shallow dish; pour marinade over top and cover tightly.
Marinate in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove roast from marinade and set aside.
Prepare charcoal fire in smoker and let burn 10 to 15 minutes.
Place water pan in smoker and fill with water.
Place roast on food rack.
Cover with smoker lid and cook 6 to 7 hours, refilling water pan and adding charcoal as needed.
Remove roast from food rack.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Slice roast thinly to serve.

title: seed munchies
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Watch that it doesn't burn.
These remind you of the Sesame Crunch candies you buy in the store.

title: hobo supper
directions: Cook in covered dish at 350° until done.

title: cherry mold(diet recipe)
directions: You will also need 6 1/2 cup mold, sprayed with Pam.

title: tenderized steak
directions: Coat steak with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in small amount of shortening.
Mix soup, onions, bouillon cubes and beef broth. Stir well.
Place in crock-pot.
Add meat.
Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours until broth thickens and steak is tender.

title: chicken rice delight
directions: In large bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon and salt until blended.
Add chicken, rice, celery and onions.
Grease a 2-quart casserole (larger for a double party size).
Place well-drained broccoli at bottom; add 1/2 of chicken; sprinkle with 1/2 the almonds; add the remaining chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and margarine around edge of the casserole and remainder of almonds in center.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
If making ahead, add crumbs and almonds at time of baking.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Scald milk and pour over 1 cup soft bread crumbs.
Mix in other ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cool and remove from bone.
Line bottom of large casserole dish with chicken.
Mix soup, broth and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Top mixture with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute scallions in butter until soft. Put frozen spinach in frying pan with scallions; cook until spinach is thawed and all water has evaporated.
In a measuring cup, put 3 eggs, then add cream or milk until liquid reaches the 1-cup mark.
Put spinach and onion mixture in a bowl; add a pinch of nutmeg and salt, then add liquid and 1/2 of Swiss cheese.
Take pie crust; put in oven for 5 minutes to firm up.
Put rest of cheese in pie crust, then pour spinach mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until a toothpick is dry when taken out.

title: old fashioned chocolate pies
directions: All people smile in the same language.

title: chili
directions: Brown chuck and onion; drain.
Boil spaghetti (small amount) in water with 1 tablespoon garlic oil, do not drain.
Combine ground chuck, spaghetti, tomato sauce, tomato soup, chili powder, salt and ginger to taste.
Add beans, if desired.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Whip egg white until foamy.
Add all ingredients and beat 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix together. Add (raw) ground beef. Rinse V-8 juice can with 1/3 cup water.
Bring to a boil. Simmer until potatoes are done.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add cheese.
Pour soup over top of chicken.
Top with Stove Top dressing (dry).
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in oven at 300° or 5 to 6 hours in crock-pot on high.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, corn syrup, margarine and pecans. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chinese chicken-noodle salad
directions: Break pasta in half and cook in boiling water for 2 minutes. Add snow peas; cook an additional minute.
Drain and rinse under cold, running water.
Drain well.
Combine pasta mixture, chicken, red bell pepper, green onion and cucumber.
Set aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lay 1 container of crescent roll dough in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together eggs, cheese and meat.
Spread on top of dough.
Place second roll of dough on top.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix well. Chill 4 hours and roll 1/2-inch.
Cut.

title: chocolate chip nut pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese evenly over bottom of crust.
Top with crabmeat.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Combine eggs with milk, salt, lemon juice or peel, and mustard.
Pour over crabmeat, top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set. Remove and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread a single layer of crackers on a buttered cookie sheet; set aside.
In a saucepan, heat butter and sugar until creamy and bubbly.
Pour butter mixture over crackers. Bake approximately 10 minutes or until mixture bubbles up.
Let cool.
Melt the chocolate chips.
Spread over cooled toffee. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Let cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: katie randall's crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in a buttered 9-inch pie pan. Double this recipe and bake in 8 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Pie will puff and then fall.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in a different bowl.
Then pour it on the butter.
Don't stir the dish up after putting everything in the dish.
Then put the peaches in and sprinkle sugar over the top and cook for about 1 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook as many beets as you plan to eat.
Skin and dice into a saucepan.
For 4 people, put them in a saucepan; add butter, sugar, vinegar and slightly thicken with flour or cornstarch. Bring to a boil and serve.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp until pink and tender; drain and cool.
Make alternate layers of shrimp and onion rings in a container with a lid that seals tightly.
Mix all remaining ingredients; heat to a quick boil and pour over the shrimp and onions.
Seal and refrigerate overnight or at least for 6 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into small strips; brown and pour off fat. Add all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes on medium heat.
Serve over rice.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook macaroni. While macaroni is cooking, melt butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted. Drain macaroni. Gently stir in cheese mixture. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Bake 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: rice custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine rice, milk, eggs, brown sugar and butter in casserole.
Place casserole in baking pan.
Fill pan with enough water to go 1/2 way up side of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir in raisins and vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Return to oven.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: christmas apple stack-cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups applesauce with each box of jello.
Layer graham crackers and jello mixture.
The red and green layers make a pretty dessert.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Mix together in a pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and buttery.

title: parmesan cheese potatoes
directions: Peel
and
cut	potatoes
into quarters.
Combine other ingredients
in a bag.
Moisten potatoes in water and shake in a bag.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning 1 time.

title: jezebel
directions: Mix and store in airtight jar in refrigerator.
Serve over block of cream cheese with crackers or bagel chips.
This will keep a long time.

title: seafood batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This can be used on fish or shrimp.
It can also be used for onion rings or chicken.
Dip in batter, then roll in a meal and flour mixture and fry.

title: cheesy crab canapes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; blend well.
Spread about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture on each muffin half.
Cut each half into quarters.
Garnish with pimento strips, if desired.
Place on baking sheets and broil 5 minutes or until crisp.
Excellent to make ahead and freeze.

title: casseroled cherry dessert(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Turn into greased, shallow 3-quart casserole or a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine undrained cherries with remaining ingredients.
Pour cherry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm or cold, topped with whipped cream or ice cream, if you like.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Add all ingredients to roasting pan. Cover and cook for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
After cooked, mash with a masher.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves several.

title: tuna noodle newburg
directions: Combine soup and evaporated milk.
Bring to boil; stir often. Remove from heat; stir in cheese, salad dressing and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir until cheese melts.
Blend in sherry.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake and cool (freeze 1/2 for another time).
Cut remaining 1/2 into 1-inch pieces.
Line 3-quart serving bowl with 1/2 the pieces.
Cover with 1/2 cup preserves, then 1/2 cup strawberries.
Spread with 1 cup whipped topping.
Repeat with remaining cake pieces, etc.
Chill.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Grate cheese; work in margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Make into 4 rolls.
Chill and slice.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Lightly brown meat; drain fat.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Can be made in crock-pot.
Good luck!

title: red wine chicken
directions: Mix everything together except chicken.
After browning chicken with flour, lay in roaster in sauce.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Use gravy over noodles.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, vanilla, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt into first mixture.
Fold in oats and then corn flakes. Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Makes a dishpan full.
Good to freeze and serve later.

title: pilot's grill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except blue cheese in blender.
Crumble blue cheese and stir in last.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add crushed wafers and milk; mix well.
Blend in the coconut and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan at 275° for 50 minutes.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 275° for 35 minutes.
The top will be soft when done.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: easy 5 salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Saute chicken and onion in margarine until lightly browned. Add cut-up broccoli, green pepper and pea pods.
Add a small amount of water and steam 7 to 8 minutes.
Add mushrooms last and continue to steam until tender.
Toss in cooked rice and serve with sour cream.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cream Cool Whip and strawberry jello.
Add crushed pineapple, cottage cheese and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Chill for several hours and serve.

title: heavenly seven layered salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread dressing over the onions, sealing it to the bowl; cover.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Garnish with bacon or shredded cheese.
Serves 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, Veg-All, soup and water.
Pour in butter.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ham crock-pot
directions: Cook potatoes according to the Stove Top directions on the box.
Layer ham, onion, potatoes, soup and margarine in the crock-pot.
Cook for 3 hours on low.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order except cheese.
Pour half of batter in a greased baking dish; add half of cheese.
Add remaining batter; cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well in a large bowl. Pour in a well greased 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes or until springs back.

title: tutti-frutti whip
directions: Mix all ingredients gently and pile into dessert dishes. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Pour onto floured board, knead for about 5 minutes.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 bottle of sauce.
Make into balls, using about 2/3 cup of mixture to make each ball.
Put meat balls in baking pan.
Pour the other bottle of barbecue sauce over meat balls.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake for about 15 or 20 minutes longer.
Can be frozen to be used later.

title: california brandy balls
directions: Mix and shape in balls size of walnuts.
Roll in more powdered sugar.
Store in tightly closed tin.
Let age at least 10 days before serving.

title: eastern shore sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix sweets and margarine.
Add Bisquick.
Mix well. Chill at least 1 hour.
You can sprinkle flour to keep dough from sticking. Roll and cut on floured board.
Pierce top of biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 24 minutes.

title: pita pizza appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly brush pita breads with Kraft House Italian dressing.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Top each pita with cheese and the listed pizza toppings, as desired.
Drizzle with additional dressing. Bake 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into quarters.

title: saucy baked beans(for crock-pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham, in crock-pot; stir well. Sprinkle ham over top, pushing half down into beans.
Cover and cook on low setting for 4 to 12 hours (on high setting for 2 to 3 hours).
Easy to increase.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in a shallow pan lined with Reynolds Wrap. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken wings. Cook at 325° and turn every 30 minutes until tender and done (usually 1 1/2 hours).
I usually make extra sauce for a richer taste and you can boil the chicken wings before they are baked to make them more tender.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
For larger quantities, add 2 cups of each ingredient.

title: three cup cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients in a baking dish.
Add fruit and bake for about 1 hour or until brown.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: 3-corn casserole
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Mix butter, sour cream and egg together. Stir in both cans of corn.
Blend in dry ingredients (muffin mix) and spoon into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake about 1 hour until golden brown and crispy on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon cheese pressed cookie(press cookie)
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese. Add sugar; cream thoroughly. Add egg, lemon juice and rind; blend well. Measure flour and baking powder together, mixing well. Add to cream cheese mixture. Mix thoroughly. Chill dough 30 minutes. Heat oven to 350°. Force dough through cookie press onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned. Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and eggs until smooth.
Mix flour, baking soda and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in oatmeal, gumdrops and coconut.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet snacks
directions: Boil together brown sugar, butter and water until sugar dissolves (medium heat).
Mix in Corn Chex, Rice Chex, Wheat Chex and pecans.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam and bake for 15 minutes at 300°.
Take out of oven; stir and bake for 10 more minutes.
Total baking time:
25 minutes.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in a small saucepan; bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and jello.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit.
Set aside to cool.
