Combine condensed milk and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Stir in gelatin mixture, then nuts.
Pour into dish and chill until firm.
This is wonderful for special occasions.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook until tender.
Set aside.
Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
In a large bowl mix stuffing mix, egg and mushroom soup.
Then add hamburger and eggplant.
Use enough of the egg plant water to mix well.
Place half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put half of cheese over mixture.
Layer remaining mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Take out 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Mix remaining with the oleo and press into pie plate.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and nutmeg in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in sour cream, egg yolks, raisins and lemon juice. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with brown sugar meringue.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Separate biscuits; place on top of pie.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, covering loosely with foil after 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in crushed Ritz crackers and nuts.
Put into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing overnight.
Grill or bake in oven.

title: grandma esther's peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter.
Mix sugar and rice cereal. Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture and blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2-inch balls and chill until firm.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Dip candies in chocolate; swirl tops.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill until firm.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Mix sour cream and pepperoni well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator for two days before serving.
This allows the sour cream to absorb the pepperoni flavor and the pepperoni to soften.

title: cheese cracks
directions: Mix cheese and margarine in mixer bowl until creamy. Add flour. Mix well. Stir in cereal and red pepper. Shape into small balls. Place on nonstick baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes about 80 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered 20 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare pastry.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat well.
Add butter. Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake until set, about 1 hour.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and powdered sugar together.
Add oil and eggs and beat.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Form balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You can dip in colored sugars before baking or add finely chopped pecans.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: cool carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots 5 to 6 minutes, still crisp and salted to taste.
Chop onion, pepper and mix other ingredients.
Add onion and pepper.
Pour over cooled carrots.
Marinate overnight.

title: louisiana bread pudding
directions: Place eggs in a mixer bowl and beat until foamy.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and allspice until evenly mixed.
Add mixture to eggs and beat until smooth.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
This is a custard base.

title: hot dog macaroni(noodle pie)
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package. Drain.
Heat oven to 350°. Mix macaroni, cottage cheese, salt, pepper, tomato pieces, Cheddar cheese and frankfurter slices.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Arrange tomato slices on top.
Mix egg, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Pour over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, until bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cold red raspberry soup
directions: Combine raspberries, wine, sour cream, sherbet and milk in blender container.
Process until well blended.
Strain, if desired.
Pour into small bowls.
Float lime slices on top.
Add several drops of fresh lime juice.
Serves 8.

title: nutty chocolate delight(4 layers)
directions: Make crust according to directions on box.
Put in a large Tupperware square and press firmly.

title: dilly beans
directions: Stem and wash green tender beans (use before beans form in hulls) and pack in hot sterilized jars.
To each jar, add a small piece of green hot pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head of dill.
Heat vinegar, water and salt to boiling.
Pour over beans.
Seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: cinnamon bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cream sugar and oil well.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add alternately flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour a small portion of batter in bottom of pans.
Sprinkle a layer of cinnamon mix over the batter.
Add another layer of batter and another of cinnamon mix; a final layer of batter.
Swirl slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle
with powdered sugar immediately after baking if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Flour, pepper and brown steak in oleo.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in consomme soup, cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally. Then stir in sour cream and cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Serve over noodles.

title: apricot-cheese delight salad
directions: Drain fruit; keep apricot and pineapple juice separate.
Chill fruit.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add the apricot juice. Fold in apricots, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until firm, then add topping.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to milk and sugar mixture. Beat egg and add to the same mixture.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in 2 more cups flour; knead until it is a smooth ball.
Place in an oiled bowl and let set in a warm place until rolls rise to double in size.
Knead down.
Roll out to 1/3-inch thick on a floured surface.
Spread soft layer of margarine.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over the top.
Roll up and pinch the seam together.
Cut and lay 1-inch apart on a cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size and bake at 375° until brown.
Glaze with powdered sugar glaze, if desired.

title: *imperial crab
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, pimiento, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce and salt together with a fork until well blended. Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Put crabmeat in large bowl and sprinkle with seafood seasoning.
Add egg mixture and mix gently.

title: busy day spaghetti
directions: Slice sausage into 1-inch pieces and brown in skillet.
Add onion and cook until onion is tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: butterscotch apple dip
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, combine milk, chips and salt. Cook and stir until chips melt. Remove from heat; stir in vinegar and cinnamon. Serve warm with apples. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate-berry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease bottom only of pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with shortening. Beat cake mix and butter in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed until crumbly; reserve 1 cup. Press remaining crumbly mixture, using floured fingers, in bottom of pan. Beat cream cheese, yogurt and frosting in same bowl on medium speed until smooth. Beat in eggs until blended. Pour into pan. Sprinkle with reserved crumbly mixture. Bake about 45 minutes or until center is set and dry to the touch. Refrigerate at least 2 hours, until chilled.

title: pizza rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Flatten out a biscuit.
Spread on 1 teaspoon of pizza sauce.
Next, add 1 slice of pepperoni and a small amount of Mozzarella cheese, then roll up biscuit into roll. Continue doing the rest of the biscuits the same way.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hershey's one-bowl buttercream frosting
directions: *One-third cup
for
light
flavor,
1/2 cup for medium flavor and 3/4 cup for dark flavor.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy stew(serving size:  6)
directions: Brown ground meat and drain; add onion, bell pepper and celery and stir until vegetables are soft.
Add tomatoes, corn, beans and water.
Season to taste.
Simmer about thirty minutes.
Recipe may be doubled.
Freezes well.

title: butterscotch pudding spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° while mixing and cooking pudding as directed on package.
Remove pudding from heat and add dry cake mix.
The mixture will be very thick, but this is normal.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and morsels.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Set aside one-half of cheese.
Cook and drain macaroni. Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Add to other mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle the 1 1/2 cups of cheese on top.
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together the butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients. Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Top with candy Kiss; press down.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: fast peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Make 12 large cookies or 24 small ones.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onions and green pepper in butter.
Set aside.
Brown meat and drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 2 quart casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at	400°
for
minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until slightly brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown meat and combine other ingredients. Pour into large greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until creamy, light and fluffy.
Beat in egg,
pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix and sift all dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate bits and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain the pineapple. Mix together.
Can add nuts, if desired.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Stir and mix.
Freeze in ice cream pan.
Stir again after 1/2 hour, 2 hours and 12 hours.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: pheasant paprika
directions: Over medium heat, melt margarine in a 10-inch skillet.
Add pheasant pieces, onion, celery, wine and water.
Sprinkle on basil, paprika and pepper.
Cover; bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer pheasant pieces for 45 minutes on both sides. After 90 minutes, remove pheasant from skillet.
Add cornstarch and sour cream to drippings; stir until thickened.
Pour over pheasant.
Serve over dumplings or noodles.

title: fried cheese
directions: Select seedless grapes and wash.
Place in Ziploc bag and freeze.
Eat frozen or defrost to go in salads.

title: herbed french bread
directions: Slice bread.
Combine soft butter, parsley flakes, onion powder and thyme leaves.
Spread between bread slices.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Blend melted margarine, flour, salt and pepper and cook over low heat until bubbling.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and cream.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in gently the chicken and sherry.
Cook slightly until well blended and heated.

title: bean pie
directions: Fry hamburger, then add chopped onion to brown.
Add soup and 1/2 can water.
Add kidney beans.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Then make up cornbread mix; pour on top of mixture and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Beat milk and egg together.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and roll in flour mixture.
Fry until brown.
Remove from oil.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix meat, cheese, broccoli and soup.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until top is brown.

title: imogene's french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add the other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Place stuffing in pockets of chops; secure with toothpicks. Brown in shortening; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chops in shallow baking pan.
Combine Heinz 57 sauce and water.
Pour over chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: turkey salad ambrosia
directions: Combine first five ingredients, set aside.
Combine last 3 ingredients and mix well. Pour over turkey mixture.
Toss gently and chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Serve in pastry shells, on lettuce leaves or as sandwiches.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except butter and cornbread crumbs.
Place in greased dish.
Top with cornbread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandmother's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream
sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs and flavoring
and blend.
Fold in dry ingredients, sifted.
Roll out on floured board
and
cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in moderate oven, about 350°.
Yields about 5 dozen, depending on size.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour in 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over top of pineapple and top with cracker crumbs. Pour melted margarine on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, zucchini, oil and sugar together.
Then add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and chopped nuts or raisins (or both).

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well and the vanilla.
Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Add all at once and mix to blend.
Don't over beat.
Set aside 1 c. batter.
Grease an 11X14 pan.
Spread all but 1 cup of the batter over the pan. Over this, spread the blueberry filling.
Top with the reserved batter by spoonfuls over the top of the filling.
Bake 30-40 minutes in 350 degree oven. Cool.
Sprinkle with powered sugar.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl with lid.
Place London broil in marinade for approximately 24 hours.
Grill London broil.
Heat marinade and serve with London broil.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake in 300° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Semi-freeze meat to make slicing easier.
Slice into 1/8-inch strips; marinate overnight.
Lay strips of meat in single layer on oven rack.
Cook at 120° for 8 to 12 hours.
Taste occasionally until desired chewiness is attained.
Makes 1/2 pound.

title: ranch chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken celery and pineapple.
Mix mayonnaise and juice for dressing.
Add to chicken mixture and toss well to coat. Chill and serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut cherries, pineapple and chopped nuts.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour mixture which is flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Then add fruits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with hot water.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter bread on one side, put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, butter side down.
Cover with sliced Jack cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Chill for 8 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be served with ham or bacon.
Also good with peaches and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: meme dessert
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks in bowl.
Beat in vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Alternate layers of crushed wafers and creamed mixture in 8-inch square baking pan until all ingredients are used, beginning and ending with crushed wafers. Chill in refrigerator.

title: toll house pan cookies(portuguese)
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, white sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in Toll House morsels and nuts.
Spread into a greased and floured cookie sheet or baking pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chinese cole slaw
directions: Put in dish and mix well.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together.
Cut each muffin into 8 quarters.
Spread each muffin with mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and freeze a couple of hours.
Place in Ziploc bags and keep frozen until ready to use.
Thaw and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown around edges.
Serve warm.
Makes 48.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, chill overnight, serve with a variety of fresh vegetables.

title: oatmeal cake and icing(fishing cake)
directions: Combine oats in boiling water. Let set 10 minutes. Add Wesson oil, eggs and sugars. Sift dry ingredients. Mix with other ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: belgian endives
directions: Trim endive root ends and separate leaves; wash thoroughly. In a skillet, melt butter and arrange endive leaves.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add lemon juice and water.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until liquid has dissolved.
Remove endive to serving dish and serve with grated cheese on top.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil on stove.
When boiled mixture is cooled a little, add next 4 ingredients, then add and mix eggs, buttermilk and nuts.
Bake in a 17 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch cookie sheet for 20 minutes (greased and floured).

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add coconut and pecans; cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk.
Beat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Layer 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in each pastry shell.
Drizzle 1/4 of caramel topping on each pie. Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture on each pie.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Put vanilla wafers
in the bottom of a dish.
Put a layer of pudding
mix with cream cheese.
Then put a layer of strawberry pie filling.
Repeat steps.
Then top with Cool Whip.

title: spam spread
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients. Add vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Mix together. If needed, more mayonnaise may be added. Makes great sandwiches and can be served on crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Makes a 2 crust 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt all ingredients except pecans.
Stir in pecans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 250°.
Stir 3 or 4 times during baking.

title: bubble ring(pull aparts)
directions: Thaw and cut each roll in half.
Arrange evenly in ungreased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Cover with Saran Wrap and tea towel.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn pan upside down over platter to dump rolls.

title: chocolate roca bars
directions: Cook butter and
sugar	until
creamy.	Lay tin foil on pan, then put crackers on.
Pour butter-sugar mixture on these and spread.
Bake
crackers
at
for 10 minutes.	Do not burn! Pour chocolate
chips
on
the crackers, spread as they melt. Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.
Cut into bars before they become too solid.
Keep refrigerated.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Then stir in chips.
Spread into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake for 23 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 16 pieces. Cool.

title: hash brown omelet
directions: In an electric frypan, fry bacon until crisp and set aside. Remove most of the grease from the pan and add hash browns.
Cook for 10 minutes and add grated cheese on top.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer and serve.

title: nana's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with salt in water.
When a little firm, cool until you can handle to peel.
Then soak the peeled, cut potatoes in mixture of wine vinegar, liquid from pickles and the pickles, chopped fine.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Add soda to milk before adding it to mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for about an hour.
Yields 2 loaves (regular size).

title: sausage-macaroni skillet
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain, rinse and set aside.
In skillet, cook sausage and green pepper until sausage is browned and pepper tender; stir occasionally to break sausage into bits and to brown evenly.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, pizza sauce and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in zucchini.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni. Cook, uncovered, for about 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy. Add egg and molasses. Beat well. Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in a different bowl. Add to molasses mixture alternately with water. Beat after each addition. Pour batter into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar when done.

title: salad
directions: Put 4 cucumbers, 6 pieces of lettuce (do not cut it up), 3 cut up tomatoes and 3 drops of salad dressing (Thousand Island) in bowl.
Cut up salad.
Then add 5 celery and 1 carrot, cut in 5 pieces.
Do not mix it up.

title: crabmeat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until just done; cool with cold water.
Cut in bite-size pieces and put in large bowl.
Boil eggs, cool and peel. Drain crabmeat and add to potatoes.
Chop some of the eggs, celery and onion and add to potatoes.
Slice radishes and add. Toss everything with mayonnaise.
Add seasoning.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Garnish with sliced eggs.

title: chili(makes 200 servings)
directions: Cook finely cut onions and meat in lard until done.
Cook spaghetti in hot water until tender.
Place remaining ingredients in large pot.
Add spaghetti, meat and onions.
Stir well and heat thoroughly.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch, flour and cocoa.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir a little of mixture into egg yolks, then blend yolks into mixture. Stir in margarine and flavoring.
Pour in pie shells.
Add meringue and bake until meringue browns.

title: chocolate fondue sauce
directions: Stir together as it heats over low heat.
Use on stove top or in a slow cooker.
When melted, pour in the center of bowl serving center.
Arrange fruits around center bowl to dip in.

title: buttermilk wheat pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and melted butter.
Pour together.
Mix until smooth. Makes 24 pancakes.

title: jalapeno corn bread muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl, mix well.
Add eggs, jalapenos, onion, oil and corn; mix well.
Gently fold in cheese.
Line cupcake pan with paper liners.
Fill 1/2 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: stew 'n' biscuits
directions: Brown meat in greased 2-quart baking dish in a 375° oven. Remove and add salt, 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce, water and onion. Cover and bake 45 minutes. Add other vegetables.
Cover and bake 45 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Prepare Bisquick dough, substituting 1/2 can tomato sauce for milk.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick. Cut into 2-inch biscuits.
Place on top of stew and bake about 20 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel and cook carrots.
Drain well. Mix other ingredients; heat until smooth.
Pour over carrots and cover.
Refrigerate.

title: dee dee's southern cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into preheated and greased pan; bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla or lemon extract.
Combine creamed mixture with flour, beating well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Boil all ingredients together for 1 hour.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss the salad ingredients together.
Add the dressing.

title: deviled stuffed eggs
directions: Remove egg shells.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove and chop egg yolks.
Dice 1 egg white.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat broth and vegetables to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Drain.

title: pickled mango
directions: Slice the mangoes into 4 quart jars.
Combine and cook the remaining ingredients until salt and sugar are dissolved.
Pour over the mangoes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat chili and stir in cream cheese thoroughly.
Serve warm or hot with taco chips.

title: fast and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet. With fork dipped in sugar, flatten cookie with crisscross design.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Bring rice and water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and water is absorbed, about 20 minutes. Combine rice with celery, onion and garlic salt.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Mix the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the milk, bananas, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix.
Line the muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill them with batter.
Bake for 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fresh fruit: grapes, strawberries and apples are very good with this.

title: family goulash
directions: Cook noodles.
While noodles cook, brown ground beef and onion together in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Stir in drained noodles, celery, catsup, mushrooms (with liquid), tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crispy texas onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Soak rings in milk for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Combine milk, egg and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Dip rings into batter and fry in hot deep oil until golden brown.

title: southern blackberry cobbler
directions: Roll out pie crust dough and place in a baking dish so that dough hangs over edges far enough to fold back over berries and seal cobbler.
Pour blackberries into crust.
Combine remaining ingredients except butter and water.
Sprinkle over blackberries. Fold the edges of dough together over the berries.
Dot with small bits of butter and pour 3/4 cup water in dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes until top is nice and brown.
Serve with whipped cream. You can substitute any berry for the blackberries.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine meat with bread crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and egg. Form into small balls.
Heat cookie sheet.
Add oil and brown meat balls on all sides.
Add water; close cover securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe and cook 5 minutes with pressure regulator rocking slowly.
Let pressure drop on its own accord.

title: steak roll
directions: Brown cubed steak on both sides.
Place stuffing mix in browned cubed steak and roll.
Put toothpicks in to hold.
Put in a baking pan and pour soup mix over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done and tender.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Mix first two ingredients well and then add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and then whipping cream beating well after each addition.
Make sure to start and finish with flour.
Add vanilla.
Spray cake pan with non-stick spray.
Put in oven at 350 degrees for 2 hours.
Do not pre-heat oven.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Slowly warm mustard and jelly until completely blended.
Put sausages in until warm.
Serve with toothpicks in a chafing dish or small crock-pot.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: maple apple yams
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until they are nearly done. Peel, slice, and place them in a buttered baking dish.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients, except whiskey.
Add whiskey.
Blend and enjoy!

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Saute onion in Dutch oven until tender.
Stir in next 5 ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until hot.
Remove from heat.
Stir in potato flakes and potatoes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Top with cracker crumbs. Dab with butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Place evaporated milk and sugar in a saucepan. Bring to rolling boil; boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly or to 238°. Remove from heat and fold in the chocolate pieces and the marshmallow cream. Stir until blended (add chopped nuts if desired). Pour into a greased pan; cool and place in refrigerator until ready to slice.

title: macaroni, cheese and tomato casserole
directions: Boil macaroni and onion together in salted water until macaroni is tender; drain.
Cube at least 1/2 pound cheese in bowl.
Add in soup and the boiled macaroni and blend together. Add to this the tomatoes.
Stir.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour covered in 400° oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° to 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Put 2 cups cornflakes and 1/2 cup margarine on top.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix with the sour cream, water and eggs.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes; jelly roll pan, 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be cut into thirds and frosted.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening (margarine or butter) and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt and mix thoroughly.
Add oats last.
Bake 35 minutes in a 12 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a large pot put enough oil to cover the bottom.
Put in chicken pieces and lightly brown.
Add garlic, onions, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook with cover on for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and cook until sauce is reduced and thick.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and 1 stick of butter together; line in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar, 2 sticks butter, eggs and vanilla; spread over cooled crust. Drain pineapple; spread over filling.
Slice bananas to cover. Put on Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Have apples, pecans and coconut ready.
Mix and sift together the flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Glaze.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Add the sugars to the softened shortening; add the vanilla and eggs.
Add the dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 x 8-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Cook spinach as directed; drain and press between paper towels.
Break egg into a mixing bowl; beat with a fork. Add spinach and cottage cheese; stir well.
Spoon 1/3 of pizza sauce into baking dish.
Place 3 uncooked lasagna noodles in a single layer over pizza sauce.
Top noodles with half of spinach mixture. Layer half of zucchini slices over spinach.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese over zucchini.
Repeat layer process ending with a top layer of pizza sauce.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sizzling steak fajitas
directions: Blend steak sauce and picante sauce.
In nonmetal dish, pour marinade over steak.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add coca, water and vanilla.
Mix well. Add oats and mix well. Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into balls; roll into confectioners sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: my grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add baking powder, salt, vanilla, almond and milk; mix well.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Using small portions of chilled dough, roll out on floured surface to 1/4 to 3/8-inch thickness. Do not roll thin.
Cut in 2-inch circles and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake cookies until lightly browned on the bottom; they will still be white on top.

title: "hot" barbecued chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips and cut wings in half.
Dust in a mixture of flour and chili powder and fry in hot oil, 8 to 10 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Heat together barbecue sauce (your choice) and hot pepper sauce.
Add the cooked chicken wings and simmer for a few minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Separate the lettuce leaves and wash under cold running water. Dry each leaf thoroughly with paper towels.
Break the romaine into
bite size pieces and scatter in the bottom of a large
salad bowl.
Add
salt,	pepper	and
olive oil; toss. Break egg yolks on top of salad; add lemon juice and mix.
Top with
croutons, anchovies and grated cheese.
Serve on chilled salad plates. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: quiche pie
directions: Combine and pour in pie crust and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes and cut.

title: presto chicken
directions: Mix everything together and marinate for 4 hours or more. When ready to cook, take
meat out of marinade and broil each side until done, basting with marinade as your broil.
Put rest of vegetables and marinade on top and broil for 5 more minutes.

title: lemon parsley sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender, cover and blend until smooth.
Brush on fish while baking, broiling or barbecuing. (Yields 1/2 cup.)

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place all in a large roaster. Bake 250 degrees for 5 hours. Keep covered but stir occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all but the last 2 ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish; top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffing(a real good stuffing for 15 to 20 pound turkey)
directions: Toast the bread slices until golden brown.
Sprinkle the baking powder over the crumbled toasted bread.
Add the poultry seasoning to bread crumbs.

title: divinity
directions: Place in saucepan over low heat the sugar, corn syrup and water.
Stir until dissolved, then cook without stirring to 255° (a little dropped into cold water forms a hard ball).
Remove from heat and pour in a fine stream into stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture holds it shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop quickly from tip of spoon onto waxed paper in individual peaks.
Makes 8 dozen pieces.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter and 1 cup of sugar in saucepan.
Mix 3/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits that have been cut in quarters.
Pack loosely in angel food pan.
Pour melted butter and sugar over biscuits.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Turn out.
Pull apart to eat.

title: fiesta bread
directions: Break biscuits into small pieces in a large bowl. Pour salsa over biscuits. Mix well. Place in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle peppers, onions and cheese over this. Bake at 350° until done in the middle.

title: rice-a-roni chicken hot dish
directions: Follow directions on package to cook Rice-a-Roni with onion. Stir in the soups and chicken.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: crabmeat oysters on the half shell
directions: Rinse oysters well and shuck.
Discard top shell; loosen oyster from bottom shell.
Arrange shell bottoms containing oysters on large baking pan.
Set in refrigerator.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Stir eggs thoroughly and mix in all other ingredients including cheeses.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is browned.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Blend well.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Stir in diced zucchini. Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Mix together Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake as soon as it comes out of oven; set aside and let cool.
Cake will soak up mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over cake; sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: party trash
directions: Melt butter and add seasonings.
Pour over cereal and nuts. Place in 250° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast berry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray or oil lightly.
Combine oats, flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar, baking powder, lemon peel and baking soda; mix well. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add buttermilk; mix just until moistened.
Knead on floured surface 10 times.
Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Form into 8-inch circle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with yogurt and combined berries and remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg; blend at low speed until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: divinity
directions: Put sugar, water and Karo syrup in saucepan and stir only until sugar dissolves.
Let cook until threads.
Put egg whites in mixing bowl and beat until stiff.
Slowly pour sugar mixture into mixing bowl with egg whites; add vanilla (you may add chopped nuts).
Beat until stiff and it will lose its shine.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1/2 can peppers.
Add drained, minced clams.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.
If sauce is too thick, add a little sour cream.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix all the above and add ice to a punch bowl and serve.

title: hot apples and cranberries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put in half of the apple pie filling, then half of whole cranberry sauce, then rest of apple pie filling.
Then top with the rest of whole cranberry sauce.
Bake to boiling hot (about 20 to 30 minutes). Serve with ham, pork, chicken or turkey.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef; spoon off excess grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, spaghetti mix and water; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chuckwagon beans
directions: Melt shortening.
Add onion, garlic and meat.
Cook until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 40 minutes.

title: favorite bread pudding
directions: Layer the bread in a baking bowl.
Sprinkle the raisins over the bread.
Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour over bread and sprinkle with a little more nutmeg.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Try to use the very thin pretzels with very little salt.
Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: excellent meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar, and water until thick and clear.
Cool completely.
A must!
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in cooled mixture.
Meringue cuts easily.
Will not shrink or weep.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Thoroughly combine ingredients in a bowl.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and place in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour mixture over margarine.
Add fruit on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: quiche
directions: Cut mild cheeses (such as Mozzarella, Provolone and a little yellow cheese), whatever meats (such as bacon, sausage or ham), mushrooms, onion and green peppers into small pieces.
Beat eggs up with fork.
Add mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper.
Put ingredients into pie crusts
with the cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with blueberry muffins and fruit.

title: congealed spring garden salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, marshmallows and water.
While this mixture is congealing, mash cream cheese and add nuts.
Add vinegar and juice from pineapple.
Then add pineapple.
Add this to the congealed mixture.
Chill.
Cut in squares and serve as salad on lettuce or as a dessert topped with Cool Whip.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk into bowl and stir well (will be lumpy).
Pour the mix into pan on top of the margarine.
Add peaches, cinnamon and nutmeg and stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until crust is brown.

title: butterscotch apple cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon to egg mixture and mix well.
Stir in apples and pecans.

title: custard pudding
directions: Make a custard mixture by turning the instant nonfat dry milk into a 1 1/2-quart bowl, adding sugar, salt, eggs and nutmeg, and beating lightly.
Add water and vanilla; stir.
Toast the bread on both sides, then spread with the butter and cut into 1-inch cubes. Arrange in a buttered baking dish holding about 6 cups.
Sprinkle the sugar, cinnamon and raisins over the toast.
Pour the custard mixture over the toast in the baking dish.
Heat the oven to 350° and bake the pudding on the center rack for 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted near the edge comes out clean.
Serves 4.

title: wassail(punch)
directions: In large pot add apple cider, cranberry juice and cinnamon sticks.
Heat slowly until it starts to froth.
Do not boil. Place whole cloves and whole allspice in a tea ball.
Dip in hot liquid to taste.
This drink is good both warm and chilled.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Mix chili and cream cheese together and heat in microwave until cheese is softened.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the grated cheddar cheese, put back in the microwave and heat until cheese is melted, mixing periodically.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken-rice-vegetable soup-stew
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together; simmer until tender, about 30 minutes. Remove chicken from broth. Strain broth and return to clean kettle. Add to boiling broth the next 8 ingredients. Cook 20 minutes or so. Add chopped chicken. Add frozen green peas. Cook until done, at least 10 more minutes. Add milk; add thickening, if desired, and adjust seasoning. If canned vegetables are used, add with chopped chicken. Serves 10.

title: yogurt dip 1-2-3
directions: Mix well and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: hot dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Good fixed in crock-pot. Serve with Doritos.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in large bowl; set aside.
In cooking pan, put oleo, shortening, cocoa and water.
Place on stove and bring just to boil.
Remove from heat and pour over sugar and flour mixture; mix lightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat all well 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour in 2 (8 x 13-inch) greased and floured pans and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: true south garden squash-pecan casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bread crumbs and nuts.
Pour into greased casserole and top with nuts and crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Really fast preparation time, can be mixed early in morning and kept in refrigerator until ready to cook.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix with strawberries.
Pour over sugar, lemon, flour, salt and butter.
Let sit while making pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Whip eggs until very light, then add milk.
Stir well and add the corn and other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and turn into a well-buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° until set and slightly brown.

title: grandma's zucchini cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix in zucchini.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in almonds and chocolate pieces.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Sieve powdered sugar over cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Use deep glass bowl.
Put Oreos in blender.
Blend until it looks like dirt.
Set aside.

title: salted peanut crisp(cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend together flour, soda and salt; stir in.
Mix in peanuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen 2 inch cookies.

title: fish salad
directions: Break fish into small pieces and combine with celery, onion and salad dressing.
Chill overnight and serve with mayonnaise on lettuce leaves.

title: mrs horton's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients as if mixing meatloaf.
Shape into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350°F for 20-30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir. Add bananas. Fold in flour and nuts. Use well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Add shortening to fat in pan to make 4 tablespoons.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and chili powder.
Stir in tomatoes and cook, stirring constantly until thick,

title: microwave teriyaki potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes with vegetable brush.
Cut tiny new potatoes into quarters or medium potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish.
Add margarine, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning and black and red peppers.
Toss to combine.
Cover; microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with rosemary and serve with sour cream.
Makes 5 side dish servings.

title: sesame stir-fry carrots
directions: Rehydrate minced onion in water for 10 minutes.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add rehydrated onion and remaining ingredients, except molasses.
Cook and stir over moderate to high heat until carrots are just crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in molasses.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shrimp cocktail spread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread in 12-inch dish or pie plate.
Scatter shrimp over cream cheese mixture.
Add layers, starting with cocktail sauce, then cheese, green onions, tomatoes and green pepper.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork roast
directions: Place roast in shallow pan. Fill half way with water. Add cut up potatoes, carrots and onion. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat begins to fall off bone.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and peanut butter to a rolling boil and stir in coconut and cornflakes.
Mix well and drop onto wax paper.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Sift flour and add alternately with wine.
Add jelly to mixture and mix well.
Add spices and vanilla.
Have fruit chopped up, add raisins and nuts.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into tube pan and bake in 300° oven for 4 1/2 hours.
This will make a 7 pound fruit cake.
Decorate cake with pineapple slices, pecans and/or cherries.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop ham and grate the Swiss cheese. Mix all ingredients except crescent rolls.
Unroll dough into 2 rectangles.
Pinch seams together. Cut rectangles in half across and then into sixths down to make 24 squares.
Place into greased mini muffin pans. Scoop mixture into each muffin hole.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute celery, onion and chestnuts.
Add flour and cook until bubbly.
Add chicken broth. Cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Then add chicken and broccoli.
Put in buttered casserole dish and top with grated cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of well greased 10 inch bundt pan and set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters; roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter and pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.
Cool bread for 10 minutes and invert on serving platter.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Combine soda, milk and banana pulp.
Add to the butter and sugar mixture. Add baking powder and flour sifted together.
Add flour and nuts. Pour into well-greased loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Cook rice as directed.
Saute onion and celery in butter until semi-soft.
Combine broccoli, rice, onion and celery.
Add soup and cheese; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: brownies
directions: Beat on medium for 3 minutes with beater.
Put in greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Mix the two types of cheese.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Form into a ball; roll in walnuts.
Chill well before serving.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 4 x 13-inch sheet pan.
In mixing bowl, mix flour and sugar;
set aside.
In saucepan, bring to a boil the water, cooking oil, butter and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute; pour over flour and sugar.
Mix.
Mix buttermilk with soda.
Pour into mixture.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and stir.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Prepare icing while cake bakes.
Ice Cake hot out of oven.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix hamburger mixture, corn, hominy, cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and crushed corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and heat to boiling.
Simmer 30 minutes until thickened.
Serve hot.

title: cherry angel cake
directions: Cut the angel food cake into pieces.
Put the cake pieces into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Then blend cream cheese (at room temperature), powdered sugar and Cool Whip in a separate bowl. Add this mixture to the cake pieces and mix well.
Then smooth out the mixture.
Add 2 cans of cherry pie filling and spread evenly. Refrigerate.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, jello and cornstarch.
Add boiling water and food coloring.
Cook
over
low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Arrange strawberries in cooked pie crust.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done, add vegetables and continue boiling until tender.
Add chicken soup and seasonings and simmer about 10 minutes.
Bake bottom pie shell until almost done.
Pour chicken mixture into pie shell and cover with other shell..
Cut slits in shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar and butter.
Add a little milk until creamy.

title: holiday almond bark
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in microwave on high 1 3/4-2 minutes until shiny.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in
half of almonds; aside. Melt chocolate bars for 1-1 1/2 minutes until shiny.
Stir in remaining almonds.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes up in chunks and put in foil.
Put a lot of butter on top, along with garlic.
Wrap up the potatoes in aluminum foil and put into oven for about 20 minutes or so.
Keep a check on them, heating at about 250° to 350°.
Bake until done.

title: baked brie with strawberries and kiwi fruit
directions: Place Brie on ovenproof platter.
Arrange fruit over top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve immediately with gingersnaps or English crackers.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring continually, until thickened.
Put in clean jars; cover with lids and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Refrigerate after opening.
This recipe came from PA.

title: low-salt italian salad(ingredients are approximate.  use more or less.)
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-size pieces and place in a large bowl.
Add seasoning, oil and vinegar.
Toss until well coated.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening in bowl.
Work in shortening with pastry blender until it forms tiny peas. Distribute water evenly over mixture.
Mix with fork.
Dough should hold together but not be sticky.
Divide in half and shape 2 balls.
Let dough sit wrapped in Saran Wrap for 2 hours before rolling out.
Makes 2 single crusts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake - bauernkuchen "farmer's cake"
directions: *Instead of shredded carrots, use 2 (7 ounce) jars of junior carrot baby food.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a 13 x 9-inch casserole pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle some Cheddar cheese on top the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: skip-a-step lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Layer uncooked noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese, 1/3 at a time, in baking dish.
Pour boiling water around edge of dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
May substitute mixture of cottage cheese and 1 egg for Ricotta cheese.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tomatoes, corn, sausage (crumbled), onion, shortening, salt and pepper in large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: danish christmas cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in extracts and vanilla. Gradually stir in flour.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Shape into 13-inch roll.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight (can be stored 2 days).
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices. Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake in 350° oven 8 minutes or to golden brown.
Remove and cool on racks.
Decorate with colored sugar or icing.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle 5 teaspoons of salt over and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next a.m. rinse mixture well and drain in colander.
Set aside.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Place cool whip in freezer first then pour in condensed milk. Next fill with chocolate milk. Do not stir mixture before placing lid on freezer. Freeze.

title: german style carrots
directions: Clean carrots and slice in 1/4-inch rounds.
Put margarine in bottom of pan.
Add carrots, onion, sugar and basil; salt and pepper, if desired.
Add no water.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Do not remove lid.
Steam in what cooks the carrots. Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cover bottom of 8-inch square pan with fruit.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, butter, baking powder, salt, milk and flour together.
Pour over fruit.
Mix remaining sugar and cornstarch; sprinkle over mixture.
Pour boiling water over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
(Can reduce amount of sugar.)

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Melt butter; add peanut butter and vanilla, then powdered sugar, a little at a time. Gets real thick. Form into egg shapes. Will make about 8. In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and wax. When completely melted, pour over egg shapes until egg is covered. After chocolate hardens, may decorate as desired.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Brown roast in hot oil in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt. Combine other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover tightly and simmer 2 hours or until fork-tender.
Remove to platter, skim off excess fat then spoon sauce over meat.
Serves 8.

title: prize-winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
In baking dish, pat into loaf shape.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lazy man's lasagne
directions: Cook ziti as directed.
While ziti is cooking, place all the other ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
When ziti is cooked (do not overcook), drain well.
Add to Ricotta mixture and mix altogether.
Place sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or glass dish.
Spoon ziti and Ricotta mixture into pan.
Top with sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover; let stand to set up.

title: jambalaya casserole
directions: *Choose 2 or more from ham, cooked chicken, cooked shrimp, Cajun or Polish sausage, cut into large dice.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Mix a German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
As soon as cake is done, poke holes all over the cake with the handle of a wooden spoon. Pour the condensed milk over the top.
Pour the ice cream topping over the top.
Cool. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Put in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
If too dry, add a small amount of water.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until lightly browned on top.
Serve with Harvard beets and apple crunch.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix in a very large bowl, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into pumpkin mixture.
Add vanilla. Fold in nuts and dates.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add mashed potatoes and beat well. Add eggs; alternate dry ingredients with sour milk and soda. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 375°.
Bake longer if necessary.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Let all ingredients cool.
Add 2 egg whites, unbeaten. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Beat until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or jello mold.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients; form ball and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Place the bulgur (crushed wheat) in bowl and cover with cold water.
Let soak for 10 minutes; then drain.
Wrap bulgur in cheesecloth and squeeze vigorously until dry.
Drop bulgur into a deep bowl; add tomatoes, parsley, onions, lemon juice and salt. Toss gently but thoroughly, mixing together with a fork.
Just before serving, stir in the olive oil and mint.
Taste for seasoning.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick of margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, 1 stick margarine and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: lebanese rice
directions: Fry and drain the first 4 ingredients.
Add water, soup mix, dry rice and melted butter; stir and cover.
Cook until rice is cooked.
Can add more water if it dries out.

title: fruit cobbler dough(this is an easy and quick dough for fruit cobblers)
directions: Melt oleo, then add all other ingredients. Pour 1/2 of the dough into a baking pan.
Add fruit and cover with rest of dough. Takes a big can of fruit or more.
Sweeten to taste; can use dewberries.
Bake at 350° until top turns brown.
Can be served with whipped topping.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, egg and milk together in bowl.
Shape into balls.
Spray pan with Pam.
Brown meatballs and drain.
Stir brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and pineapple juice in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
After boiling begins, stir for 1 minute.
Pour in meatballs.
Turn to low heat and simmer to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican dipper
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Blend cheeses and tomato sauce in crock-pot or on very low heat on stove top.
Add beef and onion mixture to cheese and tomato sauce.
Add mushrooms.
Serve warm with nachos or taco chips.

title: toffees
directions: Place sugar, water and vinegar into a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat to boil rapidly uncovered for about 15 minutes or until a small amount when poured into cold water will crack.
Remove from heat.
Stand saucepan in cold water for 1 minute.
Remove from water and allow bubbles to subside.
Pour into paper patty cups.
Leave 2 minutes and decorate with coconut or 1000's colored sugar balls.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together, then stir in milk and butter. Place on stove.
Bring to rolling boil and boil two minutes for fudge or one minute for icing.
Place in pan of cold water and beat until cool.
Add flavoring.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Don't let pretzels burn.
Remove and cool.

title: irish scones
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter with pastry blender. Stir in currants. Combine egg and half and half; add to currant mixture, stirring with fork about 15 strokes. Place dough on lightly floured board; shape into ball and knead lightly about 15 times. Divide into 2 portions. Pat each into a circle 1/2-inch thick on ungreased baking sheet. Mark in 8 wedges, cutting almost through the dough. Brush lightly with melted butter. Sprinkle with colored sugar, if desired. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sister lillian's tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in your refrigerator. Very good on potatoes or on fish.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Place cubed crackings in baking pan.
Cook in oven at 375° until crispy, but not browned.
Mix dry ingredients with milk, water and bacon drippings.
Fold in cracklings and bake 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise, cocktail sauce and mustard.
Stir in crab, celery and parsley.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 2 cups.

title: currant raisin sauce for ham
directions: Beat 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: chocolate chip cookies with walnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let butter and eggs reach room temperature.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugars and almond extract.
Beat eggs into butter and sugars.
Gradually add flour to batter until all flour has been mixed into batter.
Stir in chocolate chips; stir in nuts.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Form cookies by rolling a heaping teaspoonful of dough in palms of hands to form a ball 1 1/2 to 2 inches around.
Place on greased cookie sheets with at least 2 inches apart.
Bake one sheet at a time.
Do not regrease sheets for subsequent batches.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until dough has firmed.
Cookies will be the shape of mounds and moist inside.
Cool on racks.

title: party punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and ginger ale a punch bowl. Stir well. Add scoops of sherbet, serve. Delicious!

title: dieter's yogurt brunch
directions: Select an attractive single-serving dish.
Choose a mixture of fresh fruits which you enjoy.
Fill your dish half full with your selection of fruit, slicing large pieces and leaving whole the smaller fruits.
Add 2 to 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of vanilla yogurt.
Sprinkle dried fruit and granola on top.
Gently mix and serve.
This is best freshly made, so that the granola does not become soggy.
Try a bran muffin to complete this meal.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in skillet. Drain off fat. Salt and pepper to
taste. Add gravy mix and hot water.
Add frozen Veg-All and simmer 15 minutes. Add mayonnaise and pour into baking dish.
Put biscuits on top and bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Mash until smooth (no lumps). Add remaining ingredients, and beat until light and fluffy.
Cool. Cover and place in refrigerator. May be used any time within two weeks.
To use, place desired amount of potatoes in a greased casserole. Dot with butter and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until potatoes are heated through.

title: french fried zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into narrow strips.
Coat lightly with flour.
Dip into blended egg and water mixture.
Shake off excess. Coat again with flour.
Fry in deep fat until golden.
Drain away extra fat and spread on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with salt. Good, too, with a shake of Romano cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter; add margarine.
Make into small balls.
Place on wax paper and chill for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and wax together.
Dip balls with a toothpick into chocolate mixture.
Place back on wax paper.
Remove toothpick and with a spoon cover hole with chocolate.

title: potato and chicken casserole
directions: Place as many breasts as desired in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes over them.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well. Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then move to wire rack to cool completely. Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers in oleo and cook until they are wilted looking.
Stir in flour, mixing well.
Slowly add milk and seasoning.
Add cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and sauce thickens slightly.
Do not overcook.
Add ham and potatoes into baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat baked fish with cheese sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a shallow baking pan with nonstick coating.
Place fillets in dish, tucking under any thin edges.
Melt margarine; brush on top of fish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Cook about 8 to 10 minutes.
Used for milk or ice cream.

title: buffet beef
directions: Shake beef cubes with flour in paper bag until coated. Combine soup mix, gravy mix and ginger ale in crock-pot, mix well. Add beef cubes and remaining flour, mix well.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: coffee punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot coffee; add cinnamon sticks. Cool. Remove cinnamon sticks.
Add milk and vanilla; chill overnight. Place ice cream in punch bowl; pour coffee over ice cream 30 minutes before serving.

title: main stay french toast
directions: Cook the sugar, butter and syrup until syrupy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread apple slices over the syrup.
Place bread on top of apples.
Whisk together the remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve with spicy apple syrup.
Serves 9. Great for brunch.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Place in greased crock-pot; slice several slices of cheese on top. Sprinkle paprika on top and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours. Great for a crowd.

title: summer salad
directions: Remove rind from melons.
Slice melons into wedges.
Stem grapes.
Hull strawberries and pile in the center of a large basket or tray.
Surround with the melons, raspberries and cherries. Garnish with grapes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Simmer water, vegetables and seasoning until tender.
Don't drain.
Make white sauce (milk, oleo and flour).
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Add meat and vegetables.
Don't boil.
Serves 8.

title: hard tac candy
directions: Bring to hard ball stage, then add food coloring and 1 vial of flavoring.
Return to hard ball stage; pour onto greased cookie sheets.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine jello and sugar. Dissolve in hot water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and other ingredients.
Turn into 2-quart mold and refrigerate.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Experiment with different meats and cheeses.

title: strawberry gelatin mold
directions: 1. Boil water and add Jello to the bowl.
Add a few tablespoons of cold water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mash and add onion, salt and pepper. Add beaten eggs, milk and crumbs.
Put into a casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top with cheese and a few cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° in oven until set, lightly brown or cheese melts.

title: beef delight
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter on low.
Add steak.
Juice will accumulate.
Add all other ingredients, one at a time.
Cook until noodles are done or until desired consistency.

title: cheddar cheese balls
directions: Have cheese and butter at room temperature or leave out overnight.
Mix well until it begins to get sticky with hands. Roll into small balls.
Press with fork.
Place in freezer until frozen, then can freeze wrapped. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased pan.
Serves about 30.

title: matthew's sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, powdered sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cover.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into shapes or roll into 1-inch balls and press with thumb.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake 5 minutes or until light brown on edges.

title: guava chicken
directions: Marinate overnight and cook it over charcoal.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Measure all ingredients except flour in large mixing bowl. Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Add flour and mix with beater at speed 1 for 1 minute (blend).
Blend in food coloring if desired and fill cookie press.
Press out and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs, mashed bananas, soda, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350°.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix above; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: mock irish pie
directions: In large greased casserole dish, layer potato slices, onion and browned hamburger.
Season each layer with sprinkling of salt, pepper, powdered bouillon, powdered or minced garlic and parsley leaves.
Continue layers until casserole dish is an inch below the rim of the bowl.
Whisk mushroom soup with small amount (3 or 4 tablespoons) water until smooth and lump free.
Slowly pour over other ingredients, shaking until well covered.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with refrigerated biscuits.
Return to oven and bake at 350° until biscuits are gold.
Remove and cool slightly before serving. Serves 4.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit tarts
directions: To make festive fruit tarts for tree trimming treats, buy frozen tart shells in freezer section of your supermarket.
Make up a batch of pudding, adding milk.
Fold into pudding the cream and almond extract.
Pile pudding mixtures into tart shells.
Top with fruit slices.

title: haluski (cabbage and noodles)
directions: Cut slab bacon into small square pieces.
Chop cabbage.
Brown slab bacon and drain grease.
Add cabbage and cook until tender. Cook noodles (may substitute egg noodles or dumplings) as directed).
Drain and add to cabbage and bacon.
Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: sausage eggplant casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in skillet and add eggplant. Cook 5 minutes.
Add sausage to skillet and cook thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together onion, tomatoes and cheese, reserving a little of the cheese.
In a greased casserole, alternate layers of tomato, onion, cheese mixture with layers of eggplant, sausage mixture.
Mix crumbs with remaining cheese and sprinkle over casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: weight watchers snickers
directions: Mix together.
Mold into the shape of a candy bar.
Freeze on tinfoil.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese, slowly.
Add sugar and gradually add pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Crush about 6 cookies and mix into the pudding mixture.
Then start crushing Oreos 3 at a time.
Put some on the bottom of a plastic flower pot.
Pour mixture in.
Top with remaining crushed Oreos; looks like dirt.
Repeat until out of flower pots.
Makes about 6. Stick in silk flowers and serve with a garden tool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt the shortening in a heavy skillet.
Brown the onion and garlic.
Add meat and brown.
Add the green pepper, celery, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and cook until steaming at high heat.
Stir the mixture and sprinkle rice over the top. Do not stir after adding rice.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let sugar and baking soda stand for 20 minutes.
Scald 1 cup milk.
Cool, then add 2 beaten eggs.
Combine all with 4 1/2 cups flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 2 hours before serving.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
(Shape either as butterhorns or as pinwheels in muffin pans.)

title: potato-spinach casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cheese. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Bake yellow cake according to box in oblong pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes all over cake.
Pour on pineapple with juice. Let cake cool.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Blend until thick, then add soft cream cheese.
Blend together and pour over cake. Top with Cool Whip and store in refrigerator.

title: butterhorn yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add Crisco, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast.
Beat eggs and add to yeast and milk mixture.
Add flour.
Will make a real stiff dough. Put on floured surface and knead lightly.
Put in a large greased bowl or pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and knead slightly. Divide into 3 sections.
Roll or pat out and brush with melted butter on dough. Cut into approximately 12 wedges and roll up. Let rise again in warm place.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; refrigerate overnight. Dissolve jello in water, then add all other ingredients (including cranberries and sugar).
Refrigerate.
Ready when jelled.

title: egg timbales with cheese sauce
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and seasonings; beat again. Butter timbale molds or custard cups, and fill two-thirds full. Place in a pan of hot water and bake in a 325° oven until firm, about 25 minutes.

title: easy paella
directions: In frying pan, cook the sausages until browned; remove sausages.
Save 2 tablespoons fat and pour off the rest.
Dice onion and mince garlic; add to pan.
Cook until tender.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice, and chop the tomatoes.
Add enough stock to juice to make 3 cups.
Stir rice into onion mixture.
Add stock mixture, tomatoes, bay leaf and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken and peppers
directions: Brown chicken in margarine in a large skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to same skillet and saute until lightly browned.
Return chicken to skillet and add green pepper and tomatoes.
Pour in water and cover and simmer for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: spicy cheese ball
directions: Dice cheese and let soften at room temperature (2 hours). Dice peppers and garlic.
Put cottage cheese through blender and blend smooth; thin, if necessary, with lemon juice.
Mix all together until smooth.
Add pecans and evaporated skim milk necessary to reach desired consistency.
