Form into ball and decorate with nuts and pimento.
Chill.

title: chicken delight
directions: Saute chicken and onions in frying pan until cooked.
Place a layer of chicken on bottom of casserole dish.
Add a layer of stuffing.
Put in cream of mushroom soup (do not add water).
Add a layer of broccoli (steamed or cooked).
Spread cheese over top. Bake in oven at 350° until done (cheese is melted and broccoli is tender).

title: festive ribbon jello
directions: *Start off with deepest color (grape), then strawberry, then lime, then orange, then lemon.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this mixture for topping.
Pat remaining mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top that layer with combined peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; spread evenly.
Crumble remaining mixture over that.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Yield:
3 dozen bars.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Mix together and saute about 3 minutes.
Drain excess and refrigerate to marinate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit and serve salad dressing on top or add fruit salad dressing to moisten.
Mix with whipped cream or fruit salad dressing or salad dressing only.
May be served in orange cups.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream melted butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° until golden brown or knife comes out clean.
Do not overcook.
Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: "hi keem" (ice cream bars)
directions: Have mom or dad get one out of the freezer.
Unwrap it & eat!

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Half each tomato.
Scoop out inside of tomatoes and chop.
Mix with brown sugar, butter and salt.
Spoon mixture into tomato hulls.
Top each with bread crumbs and place into lightly greased muffin tins.
This will prevent tomatoes from rolling over.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes and serve.
Makes 12 halves.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce in pan.
Add all ingredients.
Pour in mold.
Let set in refrigerator until firm, overnight.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually with tablespoon and beat until very stiff.
Turn into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Cool.
When cool, cut off top with sharp knife.
Fill with 1/2 pint cream, whipped, into which has been folded 1 small can of drained crushed pineapple.
Put top back on in jigsaw puzzle fashion.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour and salt; stir in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet (cookies do not spread).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool. Roll in sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together well in large mixing bowl, then whip in juice which when mixed well thickens the mixture. Pour into pie shell. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: basque rice
directions: Saute bacon and onion in oil.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in a covered casserole dish at 300° until rice is done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to 235°.
Add peanuts and butter; bring to 315°, stirring constantly.
When temperature reaches 315° remove from heat and add baking soda.
Candy will fluff up fast. Mix quickly and spread thinly on a greased cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until frothy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except ginger ale.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Pour into two freezer boxes (2 quarts each). Freeze at least 24 hours.

title: old fashioned chicken pie
directions: Make up pie crust and
chill.
Boil
chicken
in
water. Debone and cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 9-inch pan or large casserole dish with the chicken.
Top with egg slices.
Melt butter;
stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add stock slowly and cook
until
thickened.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Top with rolled
out
crust.
Dot
all
over
with butter. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, approximately.

title: pumpkin nut cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin, oil and nuts.
Bake in a large tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Beat egg yolks 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar; beat.
Add butter; beat.
Add spices; beat.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Store in a plastic container in the refrigerator.
Makes lots.

title: german chocolate pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and then add other ingredients.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger, then add onions and peppers. Cook until tender. Add packet of season mix, beans, garlic powder, chili powder, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and water; mix well. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in blended sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust and cover with top crust.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.
Very good if you like raisins.

title: quick red beans and rice
directions: Make red beans and rice as package directs.
Cut the Polish sausage up and place in mixture.
Add 1/4 cup water extra, simmer until done!
As Justin Wilson would say, "I guaranteeeeeeee!!!!!!!!

title: chicken enchiladas(serves 4)
directions: Saute onions until limp; add chicken, green chilies, mushrooms, chili powder, garlic salt, 1 cup sour cream and picante sauce.
Put a good amount in center of tortillas and roll up the long way. Place 1/2 cup sour cream on bottom of baking dish.
Place flour tortillas in dish and top with remaining 1/2 cup sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated through.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain and put aside.
Saute onion with 5 tablespoons butter.
Add soup and cheese until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Put into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter and add bread crumbs to top of casserole.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice round steak thin and brown in skillet.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Ro-Tel and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for an hour.
The longer it simmers the more tender it will be, simmer with a lid on.
If liquid gets low, add some water or tomatoes.
Season according to taste.

title: blueberry cake(kids can make)
directions: Put berries in a 10 1/2 x 7 x 1-inch pan; cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts over top. Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: laingos
directions: Let yeast, pinch of sugar and milk rise.
In the middle of flour, put riced potatoes, yeast mixture, oil and salt.
Make a soft dough until smooth.
Sprinkle with flour; cover with clean dish towel.
Let rise about 1 hour (double in size).
Heat frying oil or lard.
Flatten dough pieces (size of hand), about 1/2-inch thick.
Put in hot oil and cover with lid.
Bake on one side. Take lid off and bake golden brown on other side.
Serve hot with minced garlic and salt or sugar or use your own ideas!

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, add one 4 ounce can shoestring potatoes.

title: crunchy peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and then form into balls the size of walnuts (3/4-inch).
Chill overnight.
After chilling, place chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler and melt together.
Remove peanut butter balls from fridge and dip each one in chocolate.
Place coated balls on waxed paper to harden.
When finished, it's best to store them in sealed container in refrigerator with wax paper between layers.
Makes about 90 delicious balls that melt in your mouth.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain pimentos and reserve 2 teaspoons pimentos for top.
Mix the rest in a bowl and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with taco chips.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Mash figs and bring to boil.
Cook for 10 minutes then add strawberry jello and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes, then pour in jars and seal.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on box and drain.
Mix eggs, milks, sugar, salt and butter.
Mix macaroni and shredded cheese, then add other ingredients.
Cook at 350° until slightly brown. Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: parmesan casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; cut margarine into sifted flour, sugar and salt.
Add yeast, egg and milk.
Beat well.
Stir in cheese and parsley.
Put into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Cover and let rise until double.
Dot with margarine and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jar cake
directions: Shake 2 eggs in a jar.
Add sugar, oil and orange juice. Shake well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Shake until smooth.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lekvar (prune butter) cookies
directions: Allow butter and cheese to warm; mix together.
Add flour; mix until it is like pie dough.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
On a well floured board, roll out until it is thinner than pie dough. Cut into strips about 1 1/2 x 3-inches.
Add filling to center; pinch ends together.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat eggs and then add milk.
In small bowl, sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda. Add to egg mixture and beat until smooth.
While mixing, heat oil in heavy pan to 375°.
Holding finger over bottom of a funnel, pour batter into funnel.
Remove finger and let batter pour into hot oil, swirling in circles from center outward and then drizzling just slightly over all so the cake holds together.
Fry one at a time until golden brown, turning only once.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar from sifter.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Blenderize or shake for 1 minute.
Refrigerate.
Pour on just before serving.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1 inch cubes.
Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender. Drain, reserving liquid.
Set aside potatoes.
Measure 1 cup cooking liquid, adding water, if necessary; set aside.
Peel and finely chop onion.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion to saucepan; cook, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent and tender, but not brown.
Add flour to saucepan; season with pepper flakes and black pepper to taste.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Gradually add potatoes, reserved 1 cup cooking liquid, milk and sugar to onion mixture in saucepan; stir well.
Add cheese and ham.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Store leftovers, covered, in refrigerator.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Grease a large bowl.
In another bowl, mix all ingredients and make a stiff batter.
Place dough in greased bowl and brush some oil on top of the dough.
Cover with a cloth and let set in warm place until it doubles.
Do not refrigerate!
Push dough down and knead well.
Divide into 3 or 4 loaves.
Knead each loaf 8 to 10 times.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Oil top of each loaf.
Cover and let rise until just about doubled.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Bread will sound hollow when done.
Remove from pans. Brush with butter or margarine and let cool on wire rack.

title: fruit soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a large kettle; soak overnight.
In morning, cook until tapioca is clear.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Add
food coloring to water; dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugared (coated and no syrup).
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Separate peanuts with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring at 10 minute intervals.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers and mix with other ingredients except for marshmallows and milk, then melt marshmallows and milk together. Pour over other ingredients.
Mix real good and pour in a large dish or pan.
Press until it is real firm.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican hors d'oeuvres
directions: Serve with taco chips.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Combine hot water, butter, carrots and seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil and add Stove Top Stuffing Mix.
Let stand 5 minutes. Put mixture on top of chicken breasts. Combine sour cream and cheese and put on top of dressing mix.

title: make a meal soup
directions: In a
large saucepan, brown onion in oil. Add the rest of the ingredients. Cover and simmer about 1 hour.

title: herbed asparagus
directions: Blanch asparagus in boiling water for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Remove to paper towels.
Pat dry.
In small bowl combine butter with herbs and spices.
Melt herb-butter over medium heat in large skillet.
Add asparagus.
Toss gently.
Place on serving platter. Top with shaved Parmesan cheese.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake as directed.
Let cool completely.
Slice into 4 layers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch square pan. Sift dry ingredients together into a mixing bowl.
Add egg, sugar, and molasses; mix well.
Pour boiling water and oil over mixture. Stir thoroughly until smooth.
Pour batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
While the gingerbread is still hot, pour lemon glaze (3 tablespoons lemon juice plus enough confectioners sugar to make a pourable glaze) over top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, dash of salt and melted butter.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for about 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw and rise 1 loaf of bread per instructions.
Cut up bread after it has risen into about 16 pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball and roll in butter.
Roll each ball into a mixture of brown sugar, sugar and cinnamon.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle sugar-cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits in 1/4 and roll in the sugar mixture.
Put nuts in bottom of Bundt pan.
Put cut biscuits in, sprinkling every so often with sugar mixture.
Add brown sugar to remaining sugar; mix to make 1 cup.
Combine with melted oleo.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomatoes, water and onion; bring to a boil.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is soft.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and dry ingredients and mix well. Add grated carrots and nuts until well-mixed. Bake in 9 X 13 oblong pan or 3 - 8 inch pans at 350 degrees for about 20 to 30 minutes. Cool; then put together with the following icing.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix all ingredients together.
(A food processor really is good for the mixing job.)
Spread on 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Cook in loaf pan at 300° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over cake while hot.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: chitlins
directions: Fill a large basin with cold water.
Drop in chitlins and soak undisturbed for 30 minutes.
Drain off water.
With sharp paring knife, pull off fat under running water and discard the fat from chitlins.
Rinse the meat again under cold running water and let soak for 1 hour, changing the water several times.
Rinse the meat again under cold running water and place in a large Dutch oven or stockpot.
(Chitlins must be thoroughly cleaned.)
Cover with water; add onion, vinegar, hot pepper pod, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 hours or until chitlins are fork-tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kahlua(makes 1 serving)
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add coffee.
When cool, add vodka.
Blend well.
Add vanilla bean.
Store in dark bottle tightly for 3 weeks or longer.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Pour worcestershire sauce over roast.
Place roast on a rack in a broiler pan.
Bake at 550° for 6 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 18 to 20 minutes per pound.
This will be medium rare.

title: individual raspberry cheesecakes
directions: Line 24 muffin pans with paper or foil baking cups.
Place one wafer in bottom of each pan.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat at medium speed until smooth, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Pour mixture into prepared muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Cool.
Cover pan; refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, spoon 1 heaping teaspoonful preserves over each cheesecake.
Remove paper baking cups.
Yields 24 cheesecakes.

title: onion biscuits
directions: Cook onion in hot fat until just tender.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; stir in celery seed.
Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in onion.
Combine egg and milk; add all at once to flour mixture and stir just until dough follows fork around bowl.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, salt and vanilla together.
Pour chocolate and butter into sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage, 238° and remove from heat.
Pour in vanilla and walnuts; stir until thick and creamy.
Separate with fork.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Add boiling water to mix until dropping consistency.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Press flat with fork.
Cook until slightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cut up chicken.
Place the rest of the ingredients together.
Put butter and crumbs on top.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: daddy's peanut brittle
directions: Best if cooked in iron skillet.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix together; serve with corn chips!

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
To bacon drippings, add
vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over lettuce and onion.
Toss lightly and serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: low-fat cheese lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Mix cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese; set aside. Spray a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Make 3 layers in the following order:
3 noodles, 1/3 sauce, 1/3 cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Cover tightly; cook for 1 hour.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Serve in 6 pieces.

title: green pea vegetable salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper and water in saucepan; bring to boil.
Let cool.
Mix vegetables with vinegar mixture; chill.
Will keep 10 days in refrigerator.
Yield: 12 to 14 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces on bottom of 9 x 12-inch oblong glass baking dish. Cover chicken with Swiss cheese slices. Sprinkle cubes of Stove Top stuffing (with seasoning packet) over top of cheese. Drizzle margarine over stuffing. Pour the broth over all. Cover dish with foil and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: rolled out dumplings
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour in the boiling water.
Mix with fork until well mixed.
Chill.
Must be chilled before rolling out.
On floured board, roll out 1/3 or 1/2 of mixture.
Cut in desired pieces and drop in boiling broth.

title: coating mix for chicken(tastes like kfc)
directions: Mix all together well.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Combine mustard, brown sugar, salt, pepper, catsup, vinegar and water for sauce; mix well.
Arrange pork chops in shallow dish; pour sauce over chops.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: five flavored cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Shape into balls on cookie sheet.
Dip a fork or glass in sugar and flatten each cookie. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium bowl, beat together the egg, milk and margarine.
Add egg mixture and sour cream to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch square pan coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: corn and carrots
directions: Buy amounts
to
your own size.
I cook to my taste and smell. For beginner cookers, use a pinch of seasoning.

title: surprise oyster nibbles
directions: Combine Ranch mix and oil.
Add dill weed, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers; stir to coat.
Place in warm oven (200°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out of oven; let dry and cool.
Makes a delicious snack!

title: calypso pie
directions: Blend cookies and 1/4 cup butter.
Spread evenly in 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat
egg
yolks
until
thick
and
lemon colored in a mixing bowl;
add 2 tablespoons of the milk and cream mixture. Place remainder
of
milk
and cream in a double boiler.
Set over medium heat.
Wash raisins and put in the milk mixture in the boiler.
Cook
until
soft,
about 15 minutes.
Add rice. Cook 5 minutes longer, then stir in the yolks, salt, sugar and spice. Stir until well blended, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Pour into 3-quart pudding pan.

title: goulash
directions: Brown lean ground beef with onion in a little margarine. Drain.
Add the beans, soup and water combination and the elbow macaroni.
If desired, you may add chili powder to taste.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Use 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: sweet and spicy ham
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Arrange the ham in a shallow baking pan. Score the top in a diamond pattern. Combine the pineapple juice, brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in a 2- quart heavy saucepan and mix well. Bring to a simmer. Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally. Brush the pineapple sauce over the ham. Bake for 1 to 1 & 1/2 hours or until a meat thermometer registers 130 degrees, basting frequently with the pineapple sauces. Reheat any remaining sauce and serve with ham. Makes 12 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Place spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes.

title: reese's candy balls
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, vanilla, powdered sugar and Karo syrup together until well blended by hand.
Chill.
Form ball and chill again.
Melt milk chocolate chips and paraffin together. Dip chilled balls and refrigerate.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve the dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and set aside for 15 minutes.
Mix the sugar, Crisco and salt.
Add 1 cup hot water to this and let set for 15 minutes.
Beat 1 egg in large bowl, adding all of the ingredients.
Add enough flour (approximately 4 cups) to make a soft dough.
Cover and let set for 1 hour.
Punch down and knead until like biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut out and place in buttered baking pan.
Brush tops with butter and let set until they double in size.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pollo con calabacita(mexican chicken with zucchini)
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet.
Combine next 8 ingredients; toss gently.
Spoon vegetable mixture over chicken and add water.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender and sauce is slightly thickened, stirring often.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: grandma's jelly cookies
directions: Have ready 2 1/2-inch round donut cutter and same size glass. Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to batter.
Mix well.
Roll out 1/2 dough on floured surface 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into rounds.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll out other half and cut for tops with hole in center.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with nuts and remaining sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
To assemble, spread jelly on plain rounds; put on tops.
They're as good as they look!

title: twin berry punch
directions: Combine fruits; simmer 5 minutes.
Strain, cool and chill. Blend lemonade and soda into fruit liquid.
Serves 12.

title: chicken and dumplings - country style
directions: Stew chicken until tender in 1 quart water.
Cool and remove from bone.
Cut chicken into desired pieces.
Add 1 quart water, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to simmering.

title: brown sugar pound cake with pecans
directions: Have butter, shortening and eggs at room temperature.
Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking powder and salt with
flour and add alternately with milk. Add flavorings and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pottage
directions: Soak lentils in
cold
water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Saute hamburger and onion
until	hamburger
just
loses	color
and onions are soft.
Add
this, carrots and seasonings and simmer until carrots are just done and flavors are blended.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add soda and applesauce; mix together with sifted dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If tube pan is used, bake 1 hour.

title: 12 hour salad
directions: Place salad greens in the bottom of a 3-quart bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with layers of celery, green peppers, onion and peas.
Do not toss.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream and sugar; spread over salad.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: speedy peach pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and almond extract to make a batter; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased baking dish and dot with margarine.

title: baked ziti
directions: Grease a 3-quart casserole and place 1/3 of ziti on bottom; top with 1/3 Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon 1/3 sauce over top.
Repeat layering 2 more times.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve extra sauce.
Serves 12.

title: western chili casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add 3/4 cup onion and the celery.
Saute until tender.
Add chili and seasonings.
In casserole, alternate layers beginning with chips, meat and cheese.
Top with remaining onion. Bake until hot and bubbly 15 to 20 minutes.
May prepare ahead and refrigerate.
Bake at 325° or until very hot.

title: italian pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw broccoli and drain well.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with crescent rolls.
Mix all remaining ingredients with broccoli.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 18 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: fiesta spread
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring frequently; drain.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Simmer until thickened slightly; stirring frequently.
Stir in refried beans.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese gently, leaving some cheese unmelted.
Spoon into serving bowl; top with sour cream.
Arrange lettuce and tomato around edge.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: spinach chip dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: toll house cookies(chocolate chip)
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and set aside.
mix together oleo, sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and water, stir well.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add flour mixture and mix well then add chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix well and drop by rounded 1/2 teaspoon on lightly greased
or non stick cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set about 1 minute then remove and place on paper towels. Makes about 100 cookies.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs; add buttermilk and stir in the flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Grill right away; don't let batter set.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat with a beater until well mixed. Spread between layers and on top of Carrot Cake.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In medium pan bring sugar, oleo and milk to a boil for 9 minutes.
In large bowl, mix 2 pkg. of chips and marshmallow cream.
Pour sugar mixture over chips and cream mixture until fluffy.
When slightly cool, add vanilla and pecans.
Stir well. Pour into two 9x13-inch greased pans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Sift powdered sugar and flour together 3 times. In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla with an electric mixer until soft peak forms (tips curl). Add sugar gradually about 2 tablespoons at a time, beat on high until stiff peaks form.
Sift 1/4 of flour mixture over beaten egg whites.
Gently fold the flour mixture into the beaten egg whites.
Repeat sifting and folding 1/4 flour mixture at a time until all is folded in.
Pour batter in ungreased tube pan.
Place on lowest rack of preheated oven.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Immediately invert cake in pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Loosen sides of cake from pan with a knife and remove from pan.

title: easy oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Divide ribs into serving pieces and place in roasting pan. Lay onions on top and pour over them sauce made from remaining ingredients. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven or until tender. Remove cover for the last 20 minutes and allow to brown.

title: corn sticks
directions: Grease an iron corn stick pan; place in 475° oven while preparing batter.
Combine dry ingredients in a medium bowl; add eggs, beating well.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Pour batter into preheated pan; bake at 475° until golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichokes into small pieces.
Chop green onions.
Melt butter and saute with garlic.
Mix with remainder of ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a boat out of French bread and put dip in it.
Double wrap with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: finnish coffee bread("nisu")
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm (same temperature as yeast mix).
Add yeast to milk mix.
Add 4 cups flour (enough to make a sponge). Beat thoroughly.
Rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add well beaten eggs and cardamon.
Add flour until dough is stiff enough to knead.
Let rise again to nearly double size.
Turn onto floured board and knead a few minutes.
Shape into 4 braided loaves.
Let rise to double size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven. Brush with syrup made with 1 tablespoon water and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle with coarse sugar.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and shape.
(Shape like a fish if you are creative.)
Chill before serving with your favorite crackers.

title: ya'll come scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, onions and 1 cup cheese in a lightly greased deep 3-quart casserole.
Gently stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Heat over very low heat 1/4 cup strawberry juice and marshmallows, stirring until marshmallows have melted.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup strawberry juice and add to strawberries that have been run through the blender.
Then add to the marshmallow mixture.
Cool the mixture and fold in the Dream Whip.
Mix together graham crackers, margarine and brown sugar.
Put crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving a few crumbs for sprinkling on top. Pour in strawberry mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and refrigerate or freeze.
Best when frozen and then thawed just a little.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate several hours before using.
(Do not substitute salad dressing for mayonnaise.)

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add crackers, tossing well.
Drizzle oil over cracker mixture and stir well. Place mixture in large paper bag; fold to close and let stand 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally.
Store in airtight container.

title: cranberry nut oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: french bread
directions: Spread cheese and dressing mix on bread.
Place in broiler and broil until brown.

title: great grahams
directions: Spread the graham cracker squares (as they come from the box) on cookie sheet. Combine the melted margarine and sugar. Boil 2 minutes. Spread over crackers and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 15 minutes at 275°. Remove and break crackers in sections.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix soup, vegetables and sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Mix melted butter with crackers.
Spread on the casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Fix stuffing as directed on the box. Put in bottom of baking dish.
Break chicken up and cover stuffing.
Heat soup with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° or 350°.
Crush crackers; melt butter and mix with crackers.
Cover casserole the last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place small cucumbers, a "bunch" of dill, 1 clove garlic and 1 teaspoon alum in each quart jar.
Cook water, vinegar and salt together until it boils.
Pour hot vinegar solution over and seal immediately.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Note:
I usually add diced carrots and peas.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel pears and quarter.
Place in a large pan; cover completely with sugar.
Cover with chocolate and let set overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Next day cook over medium heat until preserved, then cook slowly until dark brown.
Place in jars and seal.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix all except vanilla.
Cook on low heat until syrup forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir. Spoon out onto wax or foil paper; let cool.

title: alabama sweet potatoes
directions: Cream together potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Turn into lightly greased casserole dish.
Mix together brown sugar, melted butter, flour and pecans.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Heat soup and cream cheese to soften. Mix with spinach; add onion rings. Pour into casserole dish. Melt butter; add enough cracker crumbs to absorb butter. Spread buttered crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: molded apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Then dissolve red hot candies in 1/2 cup boiling water and add to jello mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots and
cook
4 to 5 minutes.
Drain and add rest of	ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Keeps several days.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Chill for several
hours before serving.

title: nutty coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll pie crust to 10-inch round. Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Make 1/2-inch long cuts in pastry edge at 1/2-inch intervals.
Turn back alternate pieces of pastry. Bake 9 minutes until browned.
Cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over hot carrots.
Cool. Refrigerate and stir occasionally.
Will keep well 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mom's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt cheese in a long dish or casserole bowl.
Spread broccoli on top.
Add cream of mushroom soup and rice.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Stir after about 30 minutes and so on as needed.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onion; add garlic, chicken and continue to cook until done. Add seasoning, chiles, broth, beans, cheese and sour cream.
Cook until cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.
Top each serving with cheese.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon. Set aside.
With rotary beater, beat butter and sugar together until smoothly blended.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
With a spoon, stir in vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Alternately stir the dry ingredients and milk into zucchini mixture, including nuts with the last addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about an hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: pasta prima
directions: Gradually add milk to mayonnaise.
Cook over low heat until warm.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs.
Toss with pasta until well coated.
Add bacon, cheese and parsley; toss lightly.
Serve with additional cheese, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: john clapham's bubbly cheese and bacon
directions: Crumble the cooked bacon and mix it into the cheese and butter.
Take a sheet of foil and line a cookie sheet (line anything, it's worth it).
Place the rounds evenly on the foil and broil about 4 inches from heat source.
The cheese melts, bubbles and becomes a little brown on top.
Mmmmmmmm delicious!
It will make about 50 pieces.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt and boil for 15 minutes.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: aunt sada's banana cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar, add sour cream or milk and butter and cream well.
Add beaten eggs, then mashed bananas.
Have ready the dry sifted ingredients and vanilla.
Mix and pour into a waxed-paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Serve hot with butter or ice with your favorite frosting.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Make Jiffy cake and pour into 9 x 12-inch cake pan and bake as instructed.
Mix package of pudding as box instructs; fold in cream cheese and whip until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in drained crushed pineapple and spread on top of cooled cake.
Mix Dream Whip and spread on top of pudding mixture.
Sprinkle whipped topping with crushed nuts.
Will keep in refrigerator a couple of days.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Use a coarse grader or grinder for vegetables.
Combine all vegetables in large pan.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain thoroughly in colander.
Press out all excess liquid.
Combine sugar, vinegar and seed.
Bring to a boil and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in drained vegetables and let simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Yield:
6 pints.
tags: coarse ground sweet red bell peppers

title: orange glazed beets
directions: In a saucepan, place beets and their liquid.
Heat through. In a separate saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, brown sugar and orange juice.
Cook until thickened.
Drain beets.
Stir into sauce and serve.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: An easy one-dish meal with no precooking.
Layer in 2-quart baking dish in this order:
rice, corn, sprinkle with salt and pepper, 1 can tomato sauce, 1/2 can water, onion and green pepper, ground beef, salt and pepper, second can tomato sauce and 1/4 can water.
Lay bacon strips on top.
